1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:18,885
As always, we're here today
with the national chefs of the country

2
00:00:18,952 --> 00:00:21,321
-who'll turn your fridge inside out.
-Yes.

3
00:00:21,388 --> 00:00:23,289
They're so reliable.

4
00:00:23,356 --> 00:00:25,158
What's with the grand introduction?

5
00:00:25,225 --> 00:00:26,960
Are we expecting esteemed guests?

6
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:29,929
-We're expecting special guests.
-We are?

7
00:00:29,996 --> 00:00:32,198
We're expecting a visit
from our national athletes.

8
00:00:32,265 --> 00:00:33,266
STANDBY FOR THE NATIONAL ATHLETES

9
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:36,069
APPLAUSE!

10
00:00:36,136 --> 00:00:39,406
And these athletes
were dying to meet all of you.

11
00:00:39,472 --> 00:00:41,908
-Really?
-As soon as the Olympics ended,

12
00:00:41,975 --> 00:00:44,811
they were probably bombarded
with mountains of schedule…

13
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:46,312
-Of course.
-Despite that…

14
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:47,747
"Mountains of schedule"?

15
00:00:47,814 --> 00:00:50,717
They're so busy
that even my tongue got tied.

16
00:00:50,784 --> 00:00:52,852
Anyway, before they got to anything else…

17
00:00:52,919 --> 00:00:54,721
This is a special emergency shoot,
isn't it?

18
00:00:54,788 --> 00:00:56,589
We suddenly had to summon you here.

19
00:00:56,656 --> 00:00:57,791
-He's right.
-We scheduled

20
00:00:57,857 --> 00:01:01,194
this shoot in a hurry
to be with them today.

21
00:01:01,261 --> 00:01:02,395
Let's find out who they are.

22
00:01:02,462 --> 00:01:05,498
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

23
00:01:05,565 --> 00:01:06,566
Come on out!

24
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:09,169
Should we stand up?

25
00:01:09,235 --> 00:01:10,837
Today's fridge owners!

26
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:13,373
The two golden sisters
of the Winter Olympics!

27
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:15,775
Please welcome Choi Min-jeong
and Kim Gil-li!

28
00:01:15,842 --> 00:01:18,445
Please say hello

29
00:01:18,511 --> 00:01:19,946
and take a seat.

30
00:01:20,513 --> 00:01:21,714
Come on in.

31
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:24,017
GETS UP TO BOW

32
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:27,087
-They're here.
-They have so many medals.

33
00:01:27,153 --> 00:01:29,155
She's a Korean living legend.

34
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:32,225
-Just in the Olympics.
-The Korean athlete who has won

35
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:34,394
the most medals in the Olympics,

36
00:01:34,461 --> 00:01:36,563
a living legend
in the Korean sporting world,

37
00:01:36,629 --> 00:01:38,231
please welcome Choi Min-jeong!

38
00:01:40,967 --> 00:01:42,769
A WELCOMING APPLAUSE

39
00:01:42,836 --> 00:01:45,271
Please look into the camera
and say hello to the viewers.

40
00:01:45,338 --> 00:01:46,439
LOOKING HERE AND THERE

41
00:01:46,506 --> 00:01:50,110
Hello, I'm Choi Min-jeong,
a national short track skater.

42
00:01:50,176 --> 00:01:53,012
This is my most favorite program,
so I'm very excited

43
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:55,982
and nervous to be here today.

44
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:58,251
-Thank you for joining us.
-Thank you.

45
00:01:58,318 --> 00:02:01,721
-Please welcome LamborGilli, Kim Gil-li!
-Kim Gil-li!

46
00:02:02,355 --> 00:02:03,389
Kim Gil-li!

47
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:04,791
A PASSIONATE WELCOME

48
00:02:05,058 --> 00:02:06,559
BLUSH

49
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:08,061
Please say hello to our viewers.

50
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:09,462
UH…

51
00:02:09,529 --> 00:02:10,530
AHEM!

52
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:13,533
Hello, I'm Kim Gil-li,
a national short track skater.

53
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:15,001
THE END

54
00:02:15,368 --> 00:02:16,736
A CHARISMATIC INTRODUCTION

55
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:18,972
You can say whatever you want to.

56
00:02:19,038 --> 00:02:24,811
I also have loved this program
since the first season.

57
00:02:24,878 --> 00:02:28,014
I'm so happy that I got to be here,
thanks to Min-jeong.

58
00:02:28,081 --> 00:02:30,016
I see. Is that so?

59
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:32,285
Let's give a big round of applause
to the two.

60
00:02:32,852 --> 00:02:36,456
GREAT JOB

61
00:02:36,523 --> 00:02:40,126
They're both wearing their medals.

62
00:02:40,193 --> 00:02:42,529
Can you take them off
and let us have a look?

63
00:02:42,595 --> 00:02:44,564
-Gold is expensive right now.
-I want to try it on.

64
00:02:44,631 --> 00:02:47,534
Can you tell us about the medals?

65
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,969
This is the gold
from the women's 3,000 m relay.

66
00:02:50,036 --> 00:02:51,771
-We can see which event it's for.
-Yes.

67
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:54,307
-Really?
-It's engraved in tiny letters.

68
00:02:54,374 --> 00:02:56,543
-You didn't know?
-Where is it written?

69
00:02:56,609 --> 00:02:59,412
-She has won too many.
-It's on the lower part.

70
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:01,247
FINALLY FOUND IT

71
00:03:01,314 --> 00:03:03,550
-I've never studied it closely.
-You didn't know?

72
00:03:03,616 --> 00:03:05,552
-I just found out. Did you know?
-I didn't either.

73
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:06,686
We just let them know!

74
00:03:06,753 --> 00:03:08,655
-That's how cool they are.
-It's right here.

75
00:03:09,122 --> 00:03:10,790
HOW DID I MISS THAT?

76
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:13,026
I hear they play
Odds and Evens with the medals.

77
00:03:13,092 --> 00:03:14,460
It's because you have too many.

78
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:17,230
I've seen a clip of them
throwing these like Frisbees.

79
00:03:17,297 --> 00:03:19,265
-Frisbees?
-She has that many medals.

80
00:03:19,332 --> 00:03:21,167
THE KIND OF FLEX ONLY MIN-JEONG CAN DO

81
00:03:21,234 --> 00:03:23,469
How have you been after the games?

82
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:26,272
I planned to take some time off,

83
00:03:26,339 --> 00:03:29,008
so I've been sleeping in
and eating whatever I want to eat.

84
00:03:29,275 --> 00:03:31,177
YOU'VE DONE GREAT WORK

85
00:03:31,244 --> 00:03:33,012
But you can't take a break, Gil-li?

86
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:37,016
Yesterday, I returned
to Jincheon National Training Center

87
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:39,686
and began to train again
starting this morning.

88
00:03:39,752 --> 00:03:41,287
-Gosh.
-Is there another competition?

89
00:03:41,354 --> 00:03:44,390
Yes, I must leave the country this week

90
00:03:44,457 --> 00:03:46,092
-for the World Championships.
-How fun.

91
00:03:46,159 --> 00:03:47,760
That sounds so tough.

92
00:03:47,827 --> 00:03:49,896
Can't you ask for a short break?

93
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:51,231
I want a break.

94
00:03:51,297 --> 00:03:52,432
RESPONDS IMMEDIATELY

95
00:03:53,032 --> 00:03:54,300
SHE CAN'T HIDE IT

96
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:57,337
One of the things that became a huge issue

97
00:03:57,403 --> 00:04:01,274
<i>was that the L brand</i>
<i>actually came with a car to escort you.</i>

98
00:04:01,341 --> 00:04:04,377
<i>-After all, she's nicknamed LamborGilli.</i>
<i>-LamborGilli.</i>

99
00:04:04,444 --> 00:04:05,478
<i>So they brought a car.</i>

100
00:04:05,545 --> 00:04:08,047
I was surprised to hear they were coming.

101
00:04:08,114 --> 00:04:10,883
I was like, "What? They're coming?"

102
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:14,754
When the car started,
the sound of the engine…

103
00:04:14,821 --> 00:04:16,556
-It roars.
-Yes, it was different.

104
00:04:16,623 --> 00:04:18,057
-Roar.
-Vroom!

105
00:04:18,124 --> 00:04:21,327
Back in the day, athletes paraded
in a convertible like this.

106
00:04:21,894 --> 00:04:22,996
MEMORIES OF THE GOOD OLD DAYS

107
00:04:23,062 --> 00:04:24,264
A car parade?

108
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:27,500
-They would greet everyone like this.
-One hand on the car.

109
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:31,104
I remember doing just that,
with the Korean flag in hand.

110
00:04:31,170 --> 00:04:32,739
I did this.

111
00:04:32,805 --> 00:04:34,707
You got such a nice nickname.

112
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:36,542
LAMBORGILLI RIDING THE SPORTS CAR

113
00:04:36,609 --> 00:04:39,912
We're especially grateful for Min-jeong

114
00:04:39,979 --> 00:04:44,317
for something she said
in a news interview after winning.

115
00:04:44,384 --> 00:04:47,687
She said, appearing on our show
was on her bucket list.

116
00:04:47,754 --> 00:04:49,088
-Thank you.
-She said that there.

117
00:04:49,555 --> 00:04:50,890
CHECKING OFF HER BUCKET LIST

118
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,158
-We have a clip of it.
-Yes.

119
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:54,927
A legendary skater said that about us.

120
00:04:54,994 --> 00:04:56,763
-Wait, you're playing this?
-She said it.

121
00:04:56,829 --> 00:05:00,800
<i>We hear appearing on</i> Chef & My Fridge
<i>is on your bucket list. Is that true?</i>

122
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:03,636
Chef & My Fridge <i>is my favorite show,</i>

123
00:05:03,703 --> 00:05:07,473
<i>and I love all the chefs on it too.</i>

124
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:11,778
<i>Actually, I received this box</i>
<i>of limited-edition pasta made by the IOC,</i>

125
00:05:11,844 --> 00:05:14,414
<i>and there are</i>
<i>only 2,026 boxes in the world.</i>

126
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:18,951
<i>So I want to take this back</i>
<i>and ask them to cook with this.</i>

127
00:05:19,018 --> 00:05:21,054
That was what she said.

128
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,655
This is embarrassing.

129
00:05:22,722 --> 00:05:24,891
Did we know
we were going to have her at that time?

130
00:05:24,957 --> 00:05:27,226
-No.
-No, we arranged it after the interview.

131
00:05:27,293 --> 00:05:29,195
-You called me after.
-I see.

132
00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:31,998
-Was it thanks to that interview?
-It was.

133
00:05:32,065 --> 00:05:33,700
Otherwise, you wouldn't have me.

134
00:05:33,766 --> 00:05:35,068
We didn't.

135
00:05:35,134 --> 00:05:37,170
I have won so many medals to this day.

136
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:39,505
She's right. We were awful.

137
00:05:39,572 --> 00:05:41,541
-We're sorry.
-Come to think of it, she's right.

138
00:05:41,607 --> 00:05:42,742
Didn't I tell you?

139
00:05:42,809 --> 00:05:45,144
I said I'd stop cooking
if you wouldn't invite Min-jeong.

140
00:05:45,211 --> 00:05:47,246
-You didn't.
-Okay.

141
00:05:47,313 --> 00:05:49,048
-You never said that.
-I've never heard it.

142
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:51,117
I was already watching the show

143
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:54,020
back when you invited skaters
Kwak Yoon-gy and Kim A-lang here.

144
00:05:54,087 --> 00:05:56,456
I had won a medal back then too,

145
00:05:56,522 --> 00:05:59,625
-but you never invited me.
-Oh, no!

146
00:05:59,692 --> 00:06:01,561
And not after the Beijing Olympics either.

147
00:06:01,627 --> 00:06:04,030
This time, I won once again,

148
00:06:04,097 --> 00:06:07,333
so I thought you would have me
if I mentioned it in the interview,

149
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,968
and found the courage to say that.

150
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:10,870
-Great going.
-I see.

151
00:06:10,937 --> 00:06:13,072
-I had to win seven medals to be here.
-Seriously.

152
00:06:13,306 --> 00:06:14,741
A TOTAL OF 7!

153
00:06:14,807 --> 00:06:16,242
Just for <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

154
00:06:16,309 --> 00:06:19,312
CHOKING UP
YOU DID THAT JUST FOR US?

155
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:20,913
She won the most medals ever,

156
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:22,315
and that was for our show!

157
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:23,983
BREAKING NEWS:
ALL HER MEDALS WERE FOR THIS SHOW

158
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:25,284
Her road to <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>!

159
00:06:25,351 --> 00:06:27,186
She planned it for a decade.

160
00:06:27,653 --> 00:06:30,556
AN ATHLETE CAN WAIT 10 YEARS
TO BE ON THIS SHOW

161
00:06:30,623 --> 00:06:33,826
SHE KEPT WINNING UNTIL WE CALLED,
WHICH ONLY HAPPENED AFTER 7 MEDALS

162
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:35,895
Was that pasta a part of your grand plan?

163
00:06:35,962 --> 00:06:37,397
Yes, of course.

164
00:06:37,463 --> 00:06:40,867
I was doing an interview with the IOC
just before I had one with JTBC,

165
00:06:40,933 --> 00:06:42,769
and I thought of it then,

166
00:06:42,835 --> 00:06:44,837
so I asked them for a box.

167
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:47,106
They only made 2,026 boxes
as a limited edition.

168
00:06:47,173 --> 00:06:51,077
I got the box, went to the live studio,

169
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:54,414
and showed it off
while my hands shook like this.

170
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:57,183
-I was so nervous.
-You brought the box for the interview.

171
00:06:57,417 --> 00:06:58,785
WE APPRECIATE YOUR LOVE FOR THE SHOW

172
00:06:58,851 --> 00:07:00,319
She also said this in another interview.

173
00:07:00,386 --> 00:07:03,055
"The one person on the show
I am most curious of

174
00:07:03,122 --> 00:07:04,824
is Chef Kim Poong."

175
00:07:04,891 --> 00:07:05,892
CHEF KIM POONG?

176
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:07,727
She gave a shout out to Poong.

177
00:07:07,794 --> 00:07:13,366
I'm most curious
about Chef Kim Poong's dishes.

178
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,401
-I was surprised too.
-But was there something

179
00:07:15,468 --> 00:07:18,938
you wanted to clarify
with this answer you gave?

180
00:07:19,005 --> 00:07:20,673
Well, actually…

181
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:22,775
-You can be honest.
-Yes.

182
00:07:22,842 --> 00:07:25,745
<i>The interview was done live,</i>

183
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:29,682
so Webtoon Artist Poong
was the only one that popped into my head

184
00:07:29,749 --> 00:07:32,385
as someone who makes
many interesting dishes.

185
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:34,520
So I mentioned his name there.

186
00:07:34,587 --> 00:07:37,523
-But I gave it a thought afterward…
-There was someone else.

187
00:07:37,590 --> 00:07:40,493
-…and realized that…
-It wasn't him!

188
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,295
All right, we've heard enough.

189
00:07:42,528 --> 00:07:44,363
HER CURRENT FIRST CHOICE GETS ANXIOUS

190
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:46,399
Let's continue to the next question.

191
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,034
-There's someone else?
-Who's your favorite?

192
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:51,170
-Actually, it's Chef Jong-won.
-I knew it.

193
00:07:51,237 --> 00:07:54,173
-There are many, like Chef Eun-yeong…
-Chef Eun-yeong.

194
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,142
and Chef Nam-no too.

195
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:58,244
-I love watching everyone…
-Everybody but me?

196
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:00,179
-…and all the chefs.
-She skipped over one person.

197
00:08:00,746 --> 00:08:02,548
BITTER

198
00:08:02,615 --> 00:08:04,851
-You skipped Sung-jun.
-You skipped him.

199
00:08:06,686 --> 00:08:09,355
-He won a competition too!
-He was first place.

200
00:08:09,689 --> 00:08:12,625
NO MISUNDERSTANDINGS:
MIN-JEONG LOVES ALL THE CHEFS ON THE SHOW

201
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:15,962
You suddenly couldn't think of anyone
but Poong, so you mentioned him.

202
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:20,066
I became worried,
thinking I might get to eat only his dish.

203
00:08:20,132 --> 00:08:22,668
Yes, after ten years of waiting.

204
00:08:22,735 --> 00:08:24,003
Can't let that happen after ten years.

205
00:08:24,470 --> 00:08:26,172
SHE CAN'T PUT UP WITH THAT

206
00:08:26,239 --> 00:08:27,773
But I really am curious.

207
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,243
Remember, my dishes
aren't available anywhere else.

208
00:08:30,309 --> 00:08:33,613
Eating only Poong's food
after a decade of waiting is too much.

209
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,181
-That's unfair.
-That's crazy.

210
00:08:35,248 --> 00:08:38,251
At the Milano Cortina Olympics,

211
00:08:38,317 --> 00:08:41,754
these two skaters created
many memorable moments.

212
00:08:41,821 --> 00:08:45,024
It was practically a drama.

213
00:08:45,091 --> 00:08:48,694
We won the gold at Pyeongchang
and the silver at Beijing, right?

214
00:08:48,761 --> 00:08:50,963
-Are you crying?
-I choked up.

215
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,366
-It's touching.
-It makes you cry.

216
00:08:53,432 --> 00:08:55,501
-It's so touching.
-It's very touching.

217
00:08:55,568 --> 00:08:58,638
I mean, she had 16 more laps to go.

218
00:08:58,704 --> 00:09:01,607
-Min-jeong tried not to fall!
-Exactly.

219
00:09:01,674 --> 00:09:03,776
What was on your mind?

220
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:04,877
If I fell, I knew it'd be over.

221
00:09:04,944 --> 00:09:08,848
So all I had on my mind
was that I must hold out no matter what.

222
00:09:08,915 --> 00:09:10,883
I braced myself, held out,
and came out standing.

223
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,152
After that, I began to speed up again.

224
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:14,954
-Her hand touched your blade, right?
-Yes.

225
00:09:15,021 --> 00:09:18,324
I thought she might fall,
so I hurried over to her,

226
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:21,460
but she suddenly… resurrected.

227
00:09:21,527 --> 00:09:23,429
WON THE GOLD
THANKS TO MIN-JEONG'S RESURRECTION

228
00:09:23,496 --> 00:09:25,531
The perfect plot for us

229
00:09:25,598 --> 00:09:28,634
was for me to be in second place
when I started.

230
00:09:28,701 --> 00:09:30,536
-Did you want to charge forward?
-It was our plan.

231
00:09:30,603 --> 00:09:34,473
I began to realize
I could charge and beat her.

232
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:37,310
I thought, "I will not let anyone else
take this spot."

233
00:09:37,376 --> 00:09:40,112
Most people keep balance with one hand,
but you used both.

234
00:09:40,179 --> 00:09:42,882
I did my best not to lose my place.

235
00:09:42,949 --> 00:09:45,151
And the whole country
watched your desperation.

236
00:09:45,217 --> 00:09:48,220
After that,
you competed in the 1,500 m race

237
00:09:48,287 --> 00:09:49,755
-as rivals.
-Yes.

238
00:09:49,822 --> 00:09:52,358
-We have to watch this match too.
-How sad.

239
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:55,861
Min-jeong charged forward,

240
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:57,763
then Gil-li cut inside.

241
00:09:57,830 --> 00:10:00,566
Sir, take a breather before you speak.

242
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:01,634
He got too excited.

243
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:04,870
A junior skater cut in front of her
and won overwhelmingly as first place.

244
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:08,240
And you know, we're all just human.

245
00:10:08,307 --> 00:10:09,675
She might have felt sulky.

246
00:10:09,742 --> 00:10:12,211
-It can happen. We're only human.
-Yes, we're only human.

247
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,980
She can feel that way inside.

248
00:10:14,046 --> 00:10:16,015
"How dare you pass by me?"

249
00:10:17,383 --> 00:10:19,585
You must've been mad. Be honest.

250
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:21,954
You were mad, right?

251
00:10:22,021 --> 00:10:25,091
-We're only human.
-After I took first place in the 1,500 m…

252
00:10:25,157 --> 00:10:27,460
No, I wasn't first. It was Gil-li.

253
00:10:27,526 --> 00:10:30,196
You were still thinking
that you won first place.

254
00:10:30,262 --> 00:10:32,632
-She's used to taking first place.
-After Gil-li won,

255
00:10:32,698 --> 00:10:34,700
I was happier that she had won,

256
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:37,370
-compared to someone from another nation.
-Of course.

257
00:10:37,436 --> 00:10:40,506
It's always better
for a Korean athlete to win.

258
00:10:40,573 --> 00:10:41,974
As soon as it was over,

259
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:43,676
-she ran over to celebrate.
-Yes.

260
00:10:43,743 --> 00:10:46,312
Min-jeong won seven medals

261
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:49,081
just to be here on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

262
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:52,451
This broke the record which
Shooter Jin Jong-oh, Archer Kim Soo-nyung,

263
00:10:52,518 --> 00:10:54,553
and Skater Lee Seung-hoon

264
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:57,757
had jointly held for winning six medals.

265
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:58,891
You have surpassed that.

266
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:03,396
She's now the athlete who has
the most Olympic medals in Korea.

267
00:11:03,462 --> 00:11:04,463
That's amazing.

268
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:07,133
Let me ask you a question
as a senior athlete.

269
00:11:07,199 --> 00:11:09,802
Would you like someone
to break your record?

270
00:11:09,869 --> 00:11:11,570
Or do you not want anyone to break it?

271
00:11:11,637 --> 00:11:13,706
-It'd be tough to break.
-What a question.

272
00:11:13,773 --> 00:11:16,876
All records exist to be beaten,

273
00:11:16,942 --> 00:11:18,377
and it will be.

274
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:22,682
But I hope it takes some time
before it breaks.

275
00:11:23,082 --> 00:11:24,450
HOW ADORABLE

276
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:27,053
But personally,
because I'm a short-track skater,

277
00:11:27,119 --> 00:11:30,756
I hope it's another short-track skater
who eventually breaks the record.

278
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:33,125
-Is she a likely candidate?
-She is.

279
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:35,561
Gil-li is still young too.

280
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,763
MAKING PEACE SIGNS WITH HER

281
00:11:37,830 --> 00:11:40,800
Wasn't she so cool when she entered?
This was so awesome.

282
00:11:40,866 --> 00:11:41,934
WHAT ABOUT "MY MISTAKE"?

283
00:11:42,001 --> 00:11:44,236
-Cut it out.
-Stop doing this.

284
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:46,806
-My mistake. I'll go with this now.
-"My mistake."

285
00:11:47,907 --> 00:11:50,609
Something else was talked about
as much as the matches.

286
00:11:50,676 --> 00:11:54,547
-It was Gil-li's celebration.
-What was it?

287
00:11:54,613 --> 00:11:56,615
Did you prepare that celebration?

288
00:11:56,682 --> 00:11:58,217
I thought I'd jump just once,

289
00:11:58,284 --> 00:11:59,685
but after jumping up,

290
00:11:59,752 --> 00:12:01,287
-I kept going.
-Were you happy?

291
00:12:01,353 --> 00:12:03,389
She also made me happy as a viewer.

292
00:12:03,456 --> 00:12:05,157
-I want to see it again.
-It was so energetic.

293
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:08,894
If Min-jeong had seen her celebrate,
she wouldn't have come with her.

294
00:12:10,329 --> 00:12:13,032
-Never.
-It's been a fun journey, Gil-li.

295
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,534
Aren't we glad that she hadn't seen it?

296
00:12:15,601 --> 00:12:17,036
What a relief.

297
00:12:17,103 --> 00:12:20,306
I knew something seemed odd
the moment Gil-li passed her.

298
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,008
On our show,

299
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:25,678
we also have a few young gun chefs.

300
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:27,980
What did you think
of her Gen Z celebration?

301
00:12:28,047 --> 00:12:29,715
Well, Min-jeong was there crying,

302
00:12:29,782 --> 00:12:30,983
so it was a bit much.

303
00:12:32,017 --> 00:12:33,786
Perhaps it was a bit much.

304
00:12:33,853 --> 00:12:36,655
Nam-no is the eldest among them,
so he knows what's up.

305
00:12:36,722 --> 00:12:38,124
What about you, Sung-jun?

306
00:12:38,190 --> 00:12:39,959
I thought she could've done more.

307
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:42,394
Should she have done more?

308
00:12:42,461 --> 00:12:44,163
She should've done a backflip.

309
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:46,766
At least two backflips.

310
00:12:46,832 --> 00:12:49,034
-A backflip.
-She could've done it.

311
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:51,003
The culinary world is rotten to its core.

312
00:12:52,404 --> 00:12:53,906
Don't do that. Stop nagging.

313
00:12:53,973 --> 00:12:55,574
It was fine,

314
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:56,876
until backflips!

315
00:12:56,942 --> 00:12:58,310
EXTREMELY ANGRY

316
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:02,181
This is why he always cries
in the green room.

317
00:13:02,248 --> 00:13:03,649
He's always sniffling.

318
00:13:03,716 --> 00:13:07,319
There was some sad news
soon after the Olympics.

319
00:13:07,386 --> 00:13:10,756
Min-jeong announced her retirement
from future Olympic games.

320
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:12,691
Just from the Olympics,
not as a skater, right?

321
00:13:12,758 --> 00:13:14,226
That's right.

322
00:13:14,293 --> 00:13:16,762
You're still in your prime,

323
00:13:16,829 --> 00:13:19,765
so many were surprised
that you chose to retire from the games.

324
00:13:19,832 --> 00:13:21,901
I joined the national team early on,

325
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:25,638
<i>during my first year in high school,</i>

326
00:13:25,704 --> 00:13:28,307
and my knees began to give out.

327
00:13:28,374 --> 00:13:33,279
I thought it would be too hard
to force myself to continue.

328
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:36,582
I also had many difficulties
as I prepared for the games this time.

329
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:39,852
-And it ended on a high note.
-That's important too.

330
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:44,723
-Gil-li also cried after hearing the news.
-Yes.

331
00:13:44,790 --> 00:13:46,325
How did you feel?

332
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:49,528
Whenever we trained, she'd always say,

333
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:51,730
"I need to retire now."

334
00:13:51,797 --> 00:13:53,933
It was something she often said.

335
00:13:54,633 --> 00:14:00,806
But when she said it
during an official interview,

336
00:14:00,873 --> 00:14:03,175
I got a bit emotional,

337
00:14:03,242 --> 00:14:06,645
thinking that her journey
must've been tough.

338
00:14:06,712 --> 00:14:08,714
Gil-li also went through a lot

339
00:14:08,781 --> 00:14:11,283
as we depended on each other
to prepare for the matches,

340
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:13,118
so it was very moving for me to know

341
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:16,222
that the junior skater I adore the most
would cry for me.

342
00:14:16,288 --> 00:14:19,158
So we just hugged and cried a river.

343
00:14:19,225 --> 00:14:22,494
We've always been dominant
in short track, right?

344
00:14:23,062 --> 00:14:25,798
Min-jeong has led
that powerhouse for a while,

345
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,867
and we have Gil-li,
who'll keep the reign going.

346
00:14:27,933 --> 00:14:31,136
-We can continue to be a dominant force…
-The future is bright.

347
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:33,038
-…from now on as well.
-Yes.

348
00:14:33,105 --> 00:14:34,506
-She'll keep it going.
-Great.

349
00:14:34,573 --> 00:14:37,443
And now, we'll go through the fridge

350
00:14:37,509 --> 00:14:39,678
Min-jeong and Gil-li brought.

351
00:14:39,745 --> 00:14:41,046
I only see one fridge today.

352
00:14:41,113 --> 00:14:42,715
-Not two, but one.
-Do they share it?

353
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:44,950
Our stuff is in there together.

354
00:14:45,017 --> 00:14:46,652
-But separated.
-Yes.

355
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:48,187
-Did you put them in together?
-We did.

356
00:14:48,254 --> 00:14:50,723
We both live with our family,

357
00:14:50,789 --> 00:14:53,692
so we brought the ingredients
we keep at home.

358
00:14:53,759 --> 00:14:55,527
Now, Min-jeong.

359
00:14:55,594 --> 00:14:59,565
-Did you bring that special pasta?
-Yes.

360
00:14:59,632 --> 00:15:01,100
-Here it is.
-Right here.

361
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:03,335
-That's it.
-Only 2,026 boxes.

362
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:05,804
-There are only 2,026 boxes.
-That's right.

363
00:15:05,871 --> 00:15:08,507
It's a limited-edition pasta
in the shape of the five rings,

364
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:09,942
straight from Italy.

365
00:15:10,009 --> 00:15:11,944
There are other ingredients
for Western dishes. Whose are these?

366
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:13,579
You must like Western cuisine.

367
00:15:13,646 --> 00:15:16,448
-These are brand new, not opened yet.
-They're all mine.

368
00:15:16,515 --> 00:15:20,419
I brought them from Italy just in case,
to make it easier for the chefs.

369
00:15:20,486 --> 00:15:22,755
-How considerate.
-She's so sweet.

370
00:15:22,988 --> 00:15:24,456
BROUGHT STRAIGHT FROM MILAN

371
00:15:24,523 --> 00:15:26,592
But weren't you set to be on the show

372
00:15:26,659 --> 00:15:29,762
-after you arrived in Korea?
-Wait.

373
00:15:29,828 --> 00:15:33,432
Well, I had already given that interview…

374
00:15:33,499 --> 00:15:35,334
-By that point…
-Yes, by that point…

375
00:15:35,401 --> 00:15:37,703
-…it'd be weirder for her not to come.
-She knew she'd be called.

376
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:40,005
-"Bring me on the show."
-So I went and bought those

377
00:15:40,072 --> 00:15:43,475
-right after the interview.
-"They'll have to call me now."

378
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:45,844
She's so prepared.

379
00:15:45,911 --> 00:15:47,880
-This is amazing.
-I'm so moved.

380
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,381
If she brought these ingredients,

381
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:51,050
it means she doesn't want Poong.

382
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,452
I don't see anything that I like.

383
00:15:53,752 --> 00:15:55,220
YOU GOT ME

384
00:15:55,287 --> 00:15:57,356
If she wanted him as her cook,
she would've brought

385
00:15:57,423 --> 00:15:59,458
-ingredients for chili oil.
-Something like that.

386
00:15:59,525 --> 00:16:01,627
BOO

387
00:16:01,694 --> 00:16:03,963
-These are Gil-li's, right?
-Yes.

388
00:16:04,029 --> 00:16:07,533
She has lots of ready-made products.
Rice in a cup.

389
00:16:07,599 --> 00:16:12,137
Before a match, I always have to have
that kimchi and fish roe over rice.

390
00:16:12,204 --> 00:16:13,939
-You do?
-Just before the match.

391
00:16:14,006 --> 00:16:17,876
-So I have to pack enough for the matches.
-She's going to get an ad offer now.

392
00:16:17,943 --> 00:16:19,778
Because it's hard to find Korean food?

393
00:16:19,845 --> 00:16:22,247
I don't particularly enjoy
non-Korean food,

394
00:16:22,314 --> 00:16:25,050
and I need Korean food in me
to get more energy.

395
00:16:25,117 --> 00:16:26,185
She needs to pack those.

396
00:16:26,251 --> 00:16:29,822
-So I always bring those.
-Emergency rations. Great.

397
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:32,591
Now, this fridge has
both athletes' ingredients.

398
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:34,893
What kinds of ingredients do they have?

399
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,328
Let's find out!

400
00:16:36,395 --> 00:16:37,830
-Look at that.
-That's a lot.

401
00:16:37,896 --> 00:16:39,064
They have lots of food.

402
00:16:39,131 --> 00:16:40,165
Let's find out!

403
00:16:40,232 --> 00:16:41,300
PRESENTING THEIR FRIDGE

404
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:43,769
FILLED

405
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:45,704
-Both of their ingredients.
-Combined.

406
00:16:45,771 --> 00:16:48,007
Stuff on the top shelf is mine.

407
00:16:48,073 --> 00:16:49,208
-Min-jeong's food.
-Yes.

408
00:16:49,274 --> 00:16:51,310
-The second shelf is Gil-li's.
-Gil-li's.

409
00:16:51,377 --> 00:16:52,878
On the shelf under that,

410
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:55,948
Gil-li's meat is on the left,
and mine is on the right.

411
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,484
-The meat has been separated.
-They're separated.

412
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:00,719
"Gil-li's meat, my meat."

413
00:17:00,786 --> 00:17:03,255
-Then everything on the left side is hers.
-Gil-li's.

414
00:17:03,322 --> 00:17:04,857
-The right is yours.
-The right is mine.

415
00:17:04,923 --> 00:17:08,594
You're only allowed to use the ingredients
brought by the athlete

416
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:10,996
whom you're going to cook for.

417
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:12,264
-Okay.
-Of course.

418
00:17:12,331 --> 00:17:13,599
So keep that in mind.

419
00:17:13,665 --> 00:17:15,434
That's what Min-jeong asked for.

420
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:18,037
She didn't want us to mix it up.

421
00:17:18,103 --> 00:17:19,638
She spent much more time preparing.

422
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:22,141
She spent a decade
preparing for her appearance.

423
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:23,709
-Yes, exactly.
-Let's begin.

424
00:17:23,776 --> 00:17:24,777
Let's take a look.

425
00:17:24,843 --> 00:17:27,713
The top shelf has Min-jeong's stuff.

426
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:30,449
Chicken. I found leftover fried chicken.

427
00:17:30,516 --> 00:17:31,817
Yes, everyone has that.

428
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:33,385
Do you like fried chicken?

429
00:17:33,452 --> 00:17:35,888
I don't eat deep-fried food
before a match to stay in shape,

430
00:17:35,954 --> 00:17:39,158
but the first thing I eat when I'm back
is fried chicken.

431
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:40,492
It must taste so good.

432
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:43,328
Min-jeong, what is this
about receiving fried chicken pension?

433
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:44,730
Yes, it's true.

434
00:17:44,797 --> 00:17:46,732
-What's that?
-Here's the thing.

435
00:17:46,799 --> 00:17:50,502
I can order one fried chicken a day
until the age of 60.

436
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:53,572
-What?
-What? I'm so jealous!

437
00:17:53,806 --> 00:17:55,474
SUPER JEALOUS

438
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,076
Can I have one on days you don't?

439
00:17:57,142 --> 00:17:58,644
-How many is that?
-Until you're 60?

440
00:17:58,710 --> 00:18:01,580
-Wow!
-Can you order some for us now?

441
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:02,781
HAHA

442
00:18:02,848 --> 00:18:03,849
We're hungry.

443
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:05,951
Gil-li, have you ever
had chicken with her?

444
00:18:06,018 --> 00:18:08,454
Whenever we order that brand,

445
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,289
we always get it through her.

446
00:18:10,622 --> 00:18:11,623
THE FRIED CHICKEN FAIRY

447
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:13,492
-You order it for them. How nice.
-Yes, of course.

448
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:16,028
-How do you order?
-So,

449
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:20,432
I get points in my account on the website,
and I can use them like cash.

450
00:18:20,499 --> 00:18:22,634
-You also make donations?
-Yes.

451
00:18:22,701 --> 00:18:24,536
It's too much for me to eat alone,

452
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:28,340
-so I've been donating whenever I could.
-How nice.

453
00:18:28,407 --> 00:18:29,942
-Donating sounds nice.
-I see.

454
00:18:30,008 --> 00:18:32,511
The next shelf belongs to Gil-li.

455
00:18:32,578 --> 00:18:34,613
This is the most noticeable.

456
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,048
-<i>Gejang</i> in soy sauce?
-Seasoned raw crab?

457
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,716
It's <i>gejang</i> in soy sauce.

458
00:18:37,783 --> 00:18:39,051
-<i>Gejang</i> in soy sauce.
-That's good.

459
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:40,119
Warm up some rice.

460
00:18:40,185 --> 00:18:42,754
<i>Gejang</i> in soy sauce is my favorite.

461
00:18:42,821 --> 00:18:43,889
GIL-LI LOVES GEJANG

462
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,657
So my grandma

463
00:18:45,724 --> 00:18:48,627
always makes some for me,
and we never run out.

464
00:18:48,694 --> 00:18:50,362
It's in my fridge all year round.

465
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:52,397
-You have a <i>gejang</i> pension.
-You do.

466
00:18:52,464 --> 00:18:54,233
Come to think of it, yes.

467
00:18:54,299 --> 00:18:56,268
She'll get it forever,
not until she hits 60.

468
00:18:56,835 --> 00:18:58,604
UNLIMITED SUPPLY OF GEJANG FOR LIFE

469
00:18:59,171 --> 00:19:00,873
She must really like desserts.

470
00:19:00,939 --> 00:19:01,974
DCC.

471
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:04,676
-It's Dubai chewy cookie.
-Yes, I love DCC.

472
00:19:04,743 --> 00:19:08,080
I've tried it from many different stores.

473
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:10,949
And one day, Min-jeong bought one

474
00:19:11,016 --> 00:19:13,685
for every single person
in the training center.

475
00:19:13,752 --> 00:19:16,255
-The one she got us was so delicious.
-Was it that good?

476
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:18,323
-She's so caring.
-She is.

477
00:19:18,390 --> 00:19:20,225
How could you pass her?

478
00:19:20,792 --> 00:19:22,094
Cut it out.

479
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:23,295
It was a race.

480
00:19:23,362 --> 00:19:24,997
That's what happens in short track.

481
00:19:25,063 --> 00:19:26,498
-But she was so nice.
-Yes.

482
00:19:26,565 --> 00:19:29,701
-As a soccer player, I don't get it.
-Well, I guess you won't.

483
00:19:29,768 --> 00:19:31,837
Do you also enjoy desserts, Min-jeong?

484
00:19:31,904 --> 00:19:33,739
Yes, I like DCC,

485
00:19:33,805 --> 00:19:36,542
-and I like Ggandori too.
-Ggandori?

486
00:19:36,608 --> 00:19:38,210
You watched that episode!

487
00:19:38,277 --> 00:19:40,045
-You watched it! Do you know it?
-I do.

488
00:19:40,112 --> 00:19:44,883
It's my go-to ice cream
at the snack bar of the training center.

489
00:19:44,950 --> 00:19:46,351
It's in the snack bar?

490
00:19:46,418 --> 00:19:47,886
-They have it there?
-Right? That's surprising.

491
00:19:48,287 --> 00:19:49,821
HE WANTS TO GO THERE RIGHT NOW

492
00:19:49,888 --> 00:19:51,857
-She's a true ice cream fan.
-Do you know it?

493
00:19:51,924 --> 00:19:53,792
-I don't know what it is.
-Gosh.

494
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:55,928
It's like DCC for people like us.

495
00:19:55,994 --> 00:19:57,696
-That's Ggandori.
-You're right!

496
00:19:57,763 --> 00:19:59,665
Min-jeong has been watching us.

497
00:19:59,731 --> 00:20:00,933
A TRUE CHEF & MY FRIDGE FAN

498
00:20:00,999 --> 00:20:04,269
-Meat.
-Okay. These are separated.

499
00:20:04,336 --> 00:20:06,171
This side is Min-jeong's meat.

500
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:09,107
-Strip loin, brisket. These look nice.
-Yes.

501
00:20:09,174 --> 00:20:11,510
-Do you enjoy meat?
-I love beef,

502
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:13,579
so I always make sure I have some at home.

503
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:15,781
-Loves beef.
-She eats lots of beef.

504
00:20:15,847 --> 00:20:18,417
-Meanwhile, Gil-li has pork.
-Pork.

505
00:20:18,483 --> 00:20:22,120
I prefer pork. Yes.

506
00:20:22,187 --> 00:20:23,722
I also like to eat beef,

507
00:20:23,789 --> 00:20:26,091
but I like the cuts with lots of marbling,

508
00:20:26,158 --> 00:20:30,262
such as chuck flap tail
and other special cuts.

509
00:20:30,329 --> 00:20:34,466
We received a tip from Min-jeong
about Gil-li.

510
00:20:34,533 --> 00:20:36,034
Gil-li's dream is to become

511
00:20:36,101 --> 00:20:39,371
-a mini Tzuyang.
-Tzuyang?

512
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:42,941
Whenever we eat team dinners
or eat as a group,

513
00:20:43,008 --> 00:20:46,378
Gil-li says she wants to be like Tzuyang
and claims that she can eat a lot of meat.

514
00:20:46,445 --> 00:20:47,980
-How much?
-But in actuality,

515
00:20:48,046 --> 00:20:51,783
she can't eat much more than me.

516
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:54,553
But there was one day
when she ate quite a lot,

517
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:56,521
so I thought, "She's eating well today."

518
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:58,190
Then, we got up after we were done,

519
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,225
and I saw hidden meat pieces
in front of her.

520
00:21:00,292 --> 00:21:02,361
SHE HID THE PIECES OF MEAT

521
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:04,529
HOW CUTE

522
00:21:04,596 --> 00:21:06,064
She has a cute flex about eating.

523
00:21:07,165 --> 00:21:08,433
How much do you usually eat?

524
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:11,670
I eat more than one serving.

525
00:21:11,737 --> 00:21:14,339
-What? One serving?
-One serving?

526
00:21:14,406 --> 00:21:16,441
-What do you mean?
-One serving?

527
00:21:16,508 --> 00:21:19,378
When I go to my favorite hot pot joint,

528
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:21,613
I spend at least 150,000 won.

529
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:22,681
Alone?

530
00:21:22,748 --> 00:21:24,249
Between two people.

531
00:21:24,316 --> 00:21:26,952
-That's the average.
-People usually spend that much.

532
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:29,788
-That's the usual bill.
-The hot pot franchise, right?

533
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:32,024
Did you eat hot pot
as soon as you landed in Korea?

534
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:33,692
As soon as I arrived,

535
00:21:33,759 --> 00:21:37,396
I waited for three hours
and finally got a table at 11:00 p.m.

536
00:21:37,462 --> 00:21:39,364
You drove the sports car
to a hot pot place?

537
00:21:39,431 --> 00:21:40,465
Yes.

538
00:21:42,868 --> 00:21:44,169
SHE MUST REALLY LIKE HOT POT

539
00:21:44,236 --> 00:21:47,306
I love Korean and Chinese food a lot.

540
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:48,640
PLEASED

541
00:21:48,707 --> 00:21:49,708
I see.

542
00:21:49,775 --> 00:21:51,910
Chef Eun-yeong looks quite pleased.

543
00:21:52,110 --> 00:21:53,945
THE QUEEN OF CHINESE FOOD IS HAPPY

544
00:21:54,413 --> 00:21:55,747
HEY, GIL-LI

545
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:57,783
"I see you."

546
00:21:57,849 --> 00:21:59,651
Chef Eun-yeong is happy.

547
00:21:59,718 --> 00:22:03,255
Now, the door shelf.
These belong to Min-jeong.

548
00:22:03,322 --> 00:22:05,724
-What's this? Is this from Canada?
-Maple syrup?

549
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:06,992
-It's maple syrup.
-Maple syrup.

550
00:22:07,059 --> 00:22:09,428
When I travel around the world to compete,

551
00:22:09,494 --> 00:22:12,898
I like to buy food ingredients
that are native to that country.

552
00:22:12,964 --> 00:22:16,068
I got that after a match in Canada.

553
00:22:16,134 --> 00:22:17,402
What's this?

554
00:22:17,469 --> 00:22:20,839
That's a fried chicken sauce
only sold in America.

555
00:22:20,906 --> 00:22:23,742
-That's so good.
-It's really good with chicken.

556
00:22:23,809 --> 00:22:24,810
What about this?

557
00:22:24,876 --> 00:22:27,779
That's only sold in Italy too.
It's truffle mayonnaise.

558
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:29,781
I really love truffles,

559
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:31,783
so I always get
whatever that's truffle-flavored.

560
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,552
ALWAYS GRABS TRUFFLE FLAVORS

561
00:22:33,618 --> 00:22:36,755
She's been collecting all of these
over the last decade, just for us.

562
00:22:36,822 --> 00:22:39,324
-A guest who came ready.
-Of course.

563
00:22:39,391 --> 00:22:41,927
She got maple syrup from Canada,

564
00:22:41,993 --> 00:22:45,364
something else from China, and America,
whenever she went to compete.

565
00:22:45,430 --> 00:22:46,598
That's amazing.

566
00:22:46,665 --> 00:22:48,667
Let's look at the freezer.

567
00:22:49,234 --> 00:22:51,236
You have lots of bread here.

568
00:22:51,303 --> 00:22:52,938
There are lots. Do you like bread?

569
00:22:53,004 --> 00:22:55,107
I do. I prefer bread to <i>tteok</i>, rice cake.

570
00:22:55,173 --> 00:22:57,109
I see. She's a bread person.

571
00:22:57,175 --> 00:22:58,410
And a pint of ice cream.

572
00:22:58,910 --> 00:23:00,512
I also like ice cream.

573
00:23:00,579 --> 00:23:04,249
I always have some after I eat a meal.

574
00:23:04,316 --> 00:23:07,786
And this side is Gil-li's freezer.

575
00:23:07,853 --> 00:23:10,455
-You must like dumplings.
-Yes, I do.

576
00:23:10,522 --> 00:23:12,891
-I see some rice cakes for <i>tteokbokki</i> too.
-Yes.

577
00:23:12,958 --> 00:23:15,427
You have seafood
that has your dad's love in it?

578
00:23:15,494 --> 00:23:16,595
What's that?

579
00:23:16,661 --> 00:23:19,331
I really love seafood,

580
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:24,469
so he went and caught
some webfoot octopuses himself.

581
00:23:24,536 --> 00:23:26,071
-It's in season now.
-Webfoot octopus?

582
00:23:26,138 --> 00:23:27,773
Those look good.

583
00:23:27,839 --> 00:23:30,942
So I only had webfoot octopus for a while.

584
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:32,744
I always had that whenever I went home.

585
00:23:32,811 --> 00:23:33,979
ALWAYS EATING WEBFOOT OCTOPUS AT HOME

586
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:37,249
-Was he like, "I caught these myself"?
-Yes.

587
00:23:37,315 --> 00:23:39,484
I can see how much he loves her.

588
00:23:39,551 --> 00:23:43,455
And that's it for the fridge
of the two queens of Milan.

589
00:23:43,522 --> 00:23:46,258
FINISHED CHECKING OUT
MIN-JEONG AND GIL-LI'S FRIDGE

590
00:23:46,324 --> 00:23:49,561
I wonder what
they're looking to eat today.

591
00:23:49,628 --> 00:23:52,030
Let's find out their orders.

592
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:53,198
Show us.

593
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:55,267
With Gil-li's ingredients, you'll make

594
00:23:55,333 --> 00:23:57,969
A Dish to Make LamborGilli
Slam on the Accelerator.

595
00:23:58,270 --> 00:23:59,871
SLAM ON THE ACCELERATOR?

596
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:02,474
I have a few more matches ahead,

597
00:24:02,541 --> 00:24:05,444
so I want to eat something delicious
and be full of energy.

598
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:08,647
Please help me slam on the accelerator
and continue to charge on LamborGilli

599
00:24:08,713 --> 00:24:11,082
with your delicious dish.

600
00:24:11,149 --> 00:24:13,251
So in car jargon,
you're asking for premium gas.

601
00:24:13,518 --> 00:24:14,953
THAT'S RIGHT

602
00:24:15,020 --> 00:24:16,354
What's the next order?

603
00:24:17,322 --> 00:24:20,225
Legendary Athlete's Last Dance.

604
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,260
OH, NO… THE LAST DANCE…

605
00:24:22,327 --> 00:24:23,395
What's this about?

606
00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:25,564
Until now, I had to stay on a strict diet.

607
00:24:25,630 --> 00:24:30,635
I want to eat something really delicious,
regardless of what it is.

608
00:24:30,702 --> 00:24:35,006
Also, if possible,
it'd be nice if you could make dessert.

609
00:24:35,073 --> 00:24:37,409
-Dessert too.
-I see.

610
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:39,177
She waited a decade, so she deserves it.

611
00:24:39,244 --> 00:24:41,480
-We have to do it.
-Of course, you do.

612
00:24:41,546 --> 00:24:46,518
Today,
only four people among eight get to cook.

613
00:24:46,585 --> 00:24:48,320
Who's in? First-come, first-served.

614
00:24:48,386 --> 00:24:49,788
RAISE YOUR HAND FIRST TO WIN

615
00:24:49,855 --> 00:24:52,290
-Jong-won raises his hand first.
-I knew it.

616
00:24:52,357 --> 00:24:54,125
Which one are you taking?

617
00:24:54,192 --> 00:24:56,328
While I was living abroad,

618
00:24:56,394 --> 00:24:58,997
I was often comforted
watching her compete.

619
00:24:59,064 --> 00:25:01,700
So it would be an honor to cook for her.

620
00:25:01,766 --> 00:25:02,767
Wow.

621
00:25:03,902 --> 00:25:05,370
I want to join her last dance.

622
00:25:06,571 --> 00:25:08,607
I'm so moved.

623
00:25:08,673 --> 00:25:11,743
-Whoever joins him will lose.
-Don't do it. I don't know who, but don't.

624
00:25:11,810 --> 00:25:14,713
That means Jong-won takes the first spot.

625
00:25:14,779 --> 00:25:16,748
Join quickly.
It's first-come, first-served.

626
00:25:16,815 --> 00:25:19,451
-Then I'll take it.
-Hyun-suk?

627
00:25:19,518 --> 00:25:21,820
I'd like to participate in her last dance.

628
00:25:21,887 --> 00:25:23,922
-I see.
-Diamond cut diamond.

629
00:25:24,422 --> 00:25:29,027
A round between the two of us has to be
the best performance she can expect.

630
00:25:29,528 --> 00:25:31,162
THE AVID FAN IS MOVED

631
00:25:31,229 --> 00:25:33,632
-I see.
-I'm sorry, but Chef Hyun-suk,

632
00:25:33,698 --> 00:25:35,066
will this be your last dish?

633
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:37,602
If you want,

634
00:25:37,669 --> 00:25:40,171
I will have the last dance
with my knife today.

635
00:25:41,139 --> 00:25:42,874
With his knife? No way.

636
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:44,643
No way.

637
00:25:44,709 --> 00:25:46,845
Who wants to cook for Gil-li?

638
00:25:46,912 --> 00:25:49,147
-I'll go.
-Yes, Eun-yeong should join this.

639
00:25:49,214 --> 00:25:50,582
The accelerator slammer of the show.

640
00:25:50,649 --> 00:25:52,350
I realized Gil-li and I have

641
00:25:52,417 --> 00:25:55,086
a similar taste in food
as we looked through her fridge.

642
00:25:55,153 --> 00:25:58,290
-So I think I can do this.
-I see.

643
00:25:58,356 --> 00:26:01,026
-Now, the last place.
-Eun-yeong joins the cook-off.

644
00:26:01,092 --> 00:26:03,161
We have one spot left.

645
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:05,430
THE LAST SPOT GOES TO KIM POONG

646
00:26:05,497 --> 00:26:07,966
Wait, he's a guy with broken brakes.

647
00:26:08,033 --> 00:26:10,468
I thought you might do this,
but are you sure?

648
00:26:10,535 --> 00:26:15,473
I considered joining the round
with Min-jeong's fridge,

649
00:26:15,540 --> 00:26:16,975
but after hearing her talk,

650
00:26:17,042 --> 00:26:20,445
it seemed like
she didn't particularly want me.

651
00:26:20,512 --> 00:26:23,381
-I also sit here with broken brakes…
-No brakes.

652
00:26:23,448 --> 00:26:25,083
-An eight-ton truck.
-…and continuously run,

653
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:27,519
so allow me
to slam on the accelerator today.

654
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:29,287
-All right.
-Okay, then.

655
00:26:29,354 --> 00:26:32,123
Let us begin the round for Gil-li,

656
00:26:32,190 --> 00:26:35,393
a cook-off between Chef Eun-yeong
and Webtoon Artist Poong!

657
00:26:35,894 --> 00:26:38,930
THE COOK-OFF BEGINS NOW

658
00:26:38,997 --> 00:26:43,268
<i>This is the first round</i>
<i>played with Gil-li's ingredients.</i>

659
00:26:43,335 --> 00:26:47,505
Chef Eun-yeong, who slammed
on the accelerator with Meatball Queen,

660
00:26:47,572 --> 00:26:49,507
versus Webtoon Artist Poong,

661
00:26:49,574 --> 00:26:51,710
who slammed on the accelerator
with his poop loaches.

662
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:53,945
They've both been doing well lately.

663
00:26:54,012 --> 00:26:55,614
They've been on fire,
just like LamborGilli.

664
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,382
DASHING JUST LIKE LAMBORGILLI

665
00:26:57,449 --> 00:26:59,718
But whenever
Poong goes up against Eun-yeong,

666
00:26:59,784 --> 00:27:01,720
he has been getting beaten up.

667
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:03,188
-Is that so?
-Yes.

668
00:27:03,254 --> 00:27:04,456
You've lost four times in a row.

669
00:27:04,522 --> 00:27:05,890
-Really?
-Really?

670
00:27:05,957 --> 00:27:08,259
They fought four times last year,
and Eun-yeong won them all.

671
00:27:08,326 --> 00:27:09,494
She did.

672
00:27:09,561 --> 00:27:11,396
-Please win once more.
-Once more.

673
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:14,532
How are you so strong against Poong?

674
00:27:14,599 --> 00:27:18,536
I honestly don't understand
how anyone loses against him.

675
00:27:18,603 --> 00:27:19,771
Hey!

676
00:27:21,106 --> 00:27:22,641
-You little…
-Don't you think

677
00:27:22,707 --> 00:27:24,676
you should win one soon, Poong?

678
00:27:24,743 --> 00:27:27,112
I've been doing well lately, haven't I?

679
00:27:27,178 --> 00:27:28,913
And while I'm on a roll,

680
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:30,849
I'll capture my chance to pass her.

681
00:27:31,149 --> 00:27:32,150
SLAM ON THE ACCELERATOR

682
00:27:32,217 --> 00:27:33,652
I'll pass her on the inside.

683
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:36,421
That's why I joined this round today.

684
00:27:36,488 --> 00:27:38,957
I received a report of this conversation
in the green room.

685
00:27:39,024 --> 00:27:42,260
Chef Eun-yeong said, "Gil-li and I have

686
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:44,462
many things in common."

687
00:27:44,529 --> 00:27:47,365
"Gil-li is pretty much Little Eun-yeong."

688
00:27:47,432 --> 00:27:49,367
What? This will start a controversy.

689
00:27:49,434 --> 00:27:51,670
Above all, I think it's the fun in me.

690
00:27:51,736 --> 00:27:54,339
-I see.
-And Gil-li is also known for being fun.

691
00:27:54,406 --> 00:27:58,276
Not only that, I think we also have
the same kind of taste in food.

692
00:27:58,343 --> 00:28:02,514
Whenever I watched Gil-li in matches,

693
00:28:02,580 --> 00:28:04,516
-it felt like I was watching myself.
-Why?

694
00:28:04,582 --> 00:28:06,084
This will start a controversy too.

695
00:28:06,151 --> 00:28:10,221
It's the way she passes many other skaters
and charges forward.

696
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:13,124
I'm also here with many other chefs,

697
00:28:13,191 --> 00:28:15,760
but I'm someone
who can charge whenever I want to.

698
00:28:15,827 --> 00:28:18,630
I also thought you were quite like me.

699
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:20,832
-What you said will be controversial.
-What a scoop.

700
00:28:20,899 --> 00:28:23,001
Those are my feelings! What's the problem?

701
00:28:23,068 --> 00:28:26,671
You can't try to control my feelings.

702
00:28:26,738 --> 00:28:28,940
Whoever wins today's cook-off

703
00:28:29,007 --> 00:28:30,542
gets an amazing present.

704
00:28:30,942 --> 00:28:32,310
A PRESENT?

705
00:28:32,377 --> 00:28:35,613
It's the same kit
that was given to the athletes

706
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:37,716
<i>who participated in the Olympics.</i>

707
00:28:37,782 --> 00:28:41,086
<i>The winner today will take this kit</i>
<i>which was only offered to the athletes.</i>

708
00:28:41,152 --> 00:28:43,621
-That's significant. I want it.
-There's a kit?

709
00:28:43,688 --> 00:28:46,157
<i>Gil-li will write your name</i>
<i>and give it to you.</i>

710
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:47,225
RIGHT HERE!

711
00:28:48,526 --> 00:28:50,962
-So you'll get that as a prize.
-That's awesome.

712
00:28:51,796 --> 00:28:54,199
WEBTOON ARTIST POONG'S INGREDIENTS:
SIRLOIN, BRISKET, SHRIMP, CHERRY TOMATO

713
00:28:54,265 --> 00:28:55,967
CUCUMBER, ENOKI, CHICKEN STOCK,
TUNA SAUCE, MOZZARELLA

714
00:28:56,034 --> 00:28:58,536
First, Webtoon Artist Poong.
What are you making?

715
00:28:58,603 --> 00:29:01,339
The name of the dish I'll make today is

716
00:29:01,406 --> 00:29:02,807
Kim Gil-li Pizza.

717
00:29:04,242 --> 00:29:05,410
Kim Gil-li Pizza?

718
00:29:05,477 --> 00:29:09,814
-You made use of Gil-li's celebration.
-Kim Gil-li Pizza.

719
00:29:09,881 --> 00:29:12,016
What's Kim Gil-li Pizza like?

720
00:29:12,083 --> 00:29:13,151
UH…

721
00:29:14,486 --> 00:29:18,857
There is a pizza made only for those
who do great things

722
00:29:18,923 --> 00:29:21,059
-for our country.
-Are you crazy?

723
00:29:21,126 --> 00:29:22,594
You're right.

724
00:29:22,660 --> 00:29:24,028
FOR EXAMPLE: LEE JAE-MYUNG PIZZA

725
00:29:24,095 --> 00:29:26,664
You're making that pizza?

726
00:29:26,731 --> 00:29:29,734
-I do not make this for anyone.
-It's only for state VIPs.

727
00:29:29,801 --> 00:29:31,536
It's something only made

728
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:33,972
for those who have done
great things for our country.

729
00:29:34,038 --> 00:29:37,008
-So that's Kim Gil-li Pizza?
-Yes.

730
00:29:37,075 --> 00:29:39,477
She said she loves Korean food,

731
00:29:39,544 --> 00:29:41,846
so I'll use scorched rice as the dough,

732
00:29:41,913 --> 00:29:45,717
and top it
with ingredients that she likes.

733
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:48,553
And on the very top…
She's a national athlete, right?

734
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:50,822
-I'll make the <i>Taegeuk</i> mark.
-Wow.

735
00:29:50,889 --> 00:29:52,957
-I'll top it with that.
-That's crazy.

736
00:29:53,024 --> 00:29:55,794
You'll be competing soon,
so I want to relay some good energy.

737
00:29:55,860 --> 00:29:58,696
I'll make a meaningful pizza for you.

738
00:30:00,365 --> 00:30:02,200
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:
BRISKET, TTEOKBOKKI RICE CAKE, FISH CAKE

739
00:30:02,267 --> 00:30:04,435
CHERRY TOMATO, MUNG BEAN SPROUT, SCALLION,
ENOKI, BOK CHOY, HOT POT SAUCE, AND MORE

740
00:30:04,502 --> 00:30:06,471
What are you making, Chef Eun-yeong?

741
00:30:06,538 --> 00:30:08,640
Let me explain the dish I prepared.

742
00:30:08,706 --> 00:30:12,277
She said she waited three hours
to eat hot pot, right?

743
00:30:12,343 --> 00:30:15,280
So I want to make
<i>mala tteokbokki jeongol</i> today.

744
00:30:15,346 --> 00:30:17,048
Wow. That's irresistible.

745
00:30:17,115 --> 00:30:20,118
It'll be more delicious than the hot pot
you waited three hours for.

746
00:30:20,185 --> 00:30:21,886
Just like Gil-li who won gold,

747
00:30:21,953 --> 00:30:23,521
I want to win a star today

748
00:30:23,588 --> 00:30:25,123
and continue to

749
00:30:25,190 --> 00:30:26,491
beat up Webtoon Artist Poong.

750
00:30:27,559 --> 00:30:28,560
That's why I prepared this.

751
00:30:28,626 --> 00:30:30,361
-To beat him up?
-Slamming on the accelerator.

752
00:30:30,428 --> 00:30:31,663
That sounds great.

753
00:30:31,729 --> 00:30:35,400
And now, you'll begin the round
and cook just for Gil-li.

754
00:30:35,466 --> 00:30:38,102
We'll start the timer at 15 minutes.

755
00:30:38,169 --> 00:30:40,138
The timer is ready to go.

756
00:30:40,205 --> 00:30:44,142
Today, she'll slam on the accelerator
and slam on Poong as well.

757
00:30:44,209 --> 00:30:46,811
The wildcat engine of the show,
Chef Park Eun-yeong.

758
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:50,481
This guy won't sit around
and watch Eun-yeong soar.

759
00:30:50,548 --> 00:30:54,919
The speed bump for professional chefs,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

760
00:30:54,986 --> 00:30:57,922
Which one of them
will be chosen by LamborGilli?

761
00:30:57,989 --> 00:30:59,090
And now.

762
00:30:59,157 --> 00:31:02,460
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!
Take off!

763
00:31:03,728 --> 00:31:05,830
Begin! Take off!

764
00:31:05,897 --> 00:31:07,031
SPURT

765
00:31:08,099 --> 00:31:10,401
SLAMMING ON THE ACCELERATOR
FROM THE START!

766
00:31:10,602 --> 00:31:11,603
THE GUEST LOVES IT

767
00:31:11,669 --> 00:31:12,871
He's getting cheeky again.

768
00:31:12,937 --> 00:31:14,706
You should start off smoothly.

769
00:31:14,772 --> 00:31:15,974
The start is everything.

770
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:17,542
What? Rice?

771
00:31:17,609 --> 00:31:21,246
He's using unheated instant rice.

772
00:31:21,312 --> 00:31:23,815
He's putting the rice in a pan.

773
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:25,116
-Yes.
-Like scorched rice.

774
00:31:25,183 --> 00:31:28,519
He needs to lump them together
before doing that. Will that work?

775
00:31:28,586 --> 00:31:29,754
He'll put things on top.

776
00:31:29,821 --> 00:31:31,155
They'll stick together naturally.

777
00:31:31,356 --> 00:31:33,024
HE STARTS OFF WITH CONFIDENCE

778
00:31:33,091 --> 00:31:36,094
<i>Poong seems to be doing well</i>
<i>in the beginning.</i>

779
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,595
It's important to have a good start.

780
00:31:37,662 --> 00:31:40,164
She's using scallions.

781
00:31:40,231 --> 00:31:41,399
Scallions first.

782
00:31:42,133 --> 00:31:45,703
Most Chinese chefs
tend to prep the ingredients first.

783
00:31:45,770 --> 00:31:47,772
1. PREP SCALLIONS, ENOKI,
CHERRY TOMATOES, AND BOK CHOY

784
00:31:47,839 --> 00:31:48,973
That's a must for hot pots.

785
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,141
I have a question.

786
00:31:50,208 --> 00:31:52,911
Why are you chopping off
the top of the green portion?

787
00:31:52,977 --> 00:31:54,646
I usually use that part,

788
00:31:54,712 --> 00:31:58,049
but I wanted Gil-li to eat
only the portion with a nice texture.

789
00:31:58,116 --> 00:31:59,951
ONLY THE BEST FOR GIL-LI!

790
00:32:00,018 --> 00:32:02,287
She's that considerate of the guest.

791
00:32:03,054 --> 00:32:04,055
SLAM

792
00:32:05,156 --> 00:32:06,724
PRECISION PREPPING

793
00:32:06,791 --> 00:32:08,359
Listen to that chopping sound.

794
00:32:08,927 --> 00:32:09,928
WHAT'S HIS NEXT STEP?

795
00:32:09,994 --> 00:32:11,829
It looks like he'll grind something.

796
00:32:11,896 --> 00:32:13,698
-Seasoning?
-For sauce?

797
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:15,934
He's using a lot of garlic.

798
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:20,538
He's grinding garlic, pepper,
and green onion in a blender.

799
00:32:20,605 --> 00:32:22,507
Poong, what's that for?

800
00:32:22,573 --> 00:32:24,208
It's the base for the sauce.

801
00:32:24,275 --> 00:32:25,643
Aren't you making pizza?

802
00:32:25,710 --> 00:32:27,645
What sauce do you need for pizza?

803
00:32:27,712 --> 00:32:29,113
It'll go on top of the dough.

804
00:32:29,180 --> 00:32:30,982
-Like tomato sauce.
-Instead of tomato sauce.

805
00:32:31,049 --> 00:32:33,084
He'll top the scorched rice
with that sauce.

806
00:32:33,151 --> 00:32:36,087
He's pouring oil into another pan.

807
00:32:36,154 --> 00:32:37,989
-<i>Doenjang</i>?
-He's using <i>doenjang</i>.

808
00:32:38,056 --> 00:32:39,557
It's Korean-style.

809
00:32:41,059 --> 00:32:43,528
-So that sauce will top the scorched rice?
-That's right.

810
00:32:43,594 --> 00:32:45,596
I see. It's a Korean-style pizza.

811
00:32:45,663 --> 00:32:48,399
So far, Poong's dish
looks a little more appetizing.

812
00:32:48,466 --> 00:32:51,336
-Red pepper powder.
-His dish looks delicious.

813
00:32:51,402 --> 00:32:53,705
It's been three minutes.

814
00:32:53,771 --> 00:32:56,341
-You need to pull together now.
-Pull together!

815
00:32:56,407 --> 00:32:57,976
She had a hot pot sauce.

816
00:32:58,042 --> 00:32:59,978
-The hot pot sauce?
-The packaged one?

817
00:33:00,044 --> 00:33:03,047
-She added scallions.
-I'm stir-frying them with garlic.

818
00:33:03,114 --> 00:33:04,449
-Cooking wine.
-Cooking wine.

819
00:33:04,515 --> 00:33:06,684
What are you making, Eun-yeong?

820
00:33:06,751 --> 00:33:08,486
<i>Tteokbokki</i> base, the broth.

821
00:33:08,553 --> 00:33:10,655
-The broth.
-The base for <i>mala tteokbokki</i>.

822
00:33:10,722 --> 00:33:13,124
3. ADD BOK CHOY, ENOKI,
AND MORE HOT POT SAUCE TO THE PAN

823
00:33:14,392 --> 00:33:15,426
Gochujang?

824
00:33:15,493 --> 00:33:17,595
She's adding gochujang to hot pot?

825
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:19,163
She called it <i>tteokbokki</i>.

826
00:33:20,732 --> 00:33:21,966
ADDING HOT WATER TO MAKE BROTH!

827
00:33:22,033 --> 00:33:24,102
It looks like spicy soup.

828
00:33:24,168 --> 00:33:26,537
-It looks good.
-It smells great.

829
00:33:26,604 --> 00:33:31,042
<i>Eun-yeong is right behind,</i>
<i>but Poong continues to keep his lead.</i>

830
00:33:31,109 --> 00:33:33,177
You should try to keep a good pace.

831
00:33:33,244 --> 00:33:34,245
Sirloin and brisket.

832
00:33:34,312 --> 00:33:36,280
He grinds sirloin and brisket together.

833
00:33:37,081 --> 00:33:38,216
Excellent.

834
00:33:38,282 --> 00:33:40,418
-Excellent! I'll keep charging ahead.
-That's good.

835
00:33:40,918 --> 00:33:42,754
LOOKING PRETTY GOOD

836
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:47,025
3. ADD SOY SAUCE, CHICKEN STOCK,
TUNA SAUCE, VINEGAR, AND SESAME OIL

837
00:33:47,091 --> 00:33:48,092
Even some sesame oil.

838
00:33:48,826 --> 00:33:50,728
He puts on a fire show.

839
00:33:50,795 --> 00:33:53,664
-It's on fire.
-The pan is on fire.

840
00:33:54,465 --> 00:33:56,300
TASTING!

841
00:33:56,534 --> 00:33:57,535
GOOD!

842
00:33:57,969 --> 00:33:59,170
ADDING COOKING WINE

843
00:33:59,237 --> 00:34:00,238
That looks good.

844
00:34:00,304 --> 00:34:01,906
You said you'd make the <i>Taegeuk</i> mark.

845
00:34:01,973 --> 00:34:04,242
Is that for the red part?

846
00:34:04,308 --> 00:34:05,710
-How will you make it blue?
-Right?

847
00:34:05,777 --> 00:34:08,446
You can create the color red with food…

848
00:34:08,513 --> 00:34:10,014
-Blue?
-…but as for blue…

849
00:34:10,081 --> 00:34:12,817
-There isn't much he can do.
-There's nothing.

850
00:34:14,318 --> 00:34:16,054
I think he's using a cucumber for that.

851
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:17,955
-Are you using a cucumber to add blue?
-Yes.

852
00:34:18,923 --> 00:34:20,792
He'll make the color blue with a cucumber.

853
00:34:20,858 --> 00:34:22,126
Do you like cucumbers?

854
00:34:22,193 --> 00:34:23,461
-I do.
-You do?

855
00:34:23,528 --> 00:34:26,364
-Do you?
-But I've never had it on pizza.

856
00:34:26,431 --> 00:34:28,633
She has never had cucumber on pizza.

857
00:34:28,699 --> 00:34:30,501
-Cucumber on pizza?
-Cucumber?

858
00:34:30,568 --> 00:34:31,569
Cucumber pizza is a bit…

859
00:34:31,636 --> 00:34:33,604
He's grinding that too.

860
00:34:33,671 --> 00:34:34,972
Is ground cucumber the topping?

861
00:34:35,306 --> 00:34:37,141
THAT'LL BE CONTROVERSIAL

862
00:34:37,208 --> 00:34:40,078
Chef Eun-yeong should hurry
and start her chase.

863
00:34:40,645 --> 00:34:42,447
Are you topping brisket
on mung bean sprouts?

864
00:34:42,513 --> 00:34:44,682
I am. I'm making <i>jeongol</i>, Korean hot pot.

865
00:34:44,749 --> 00:34:46,951
PILE UP LIKE A MOUNTAIN!

866
00:34:47,018 --> 00:34:49,654
-You said it was <i>mala tteokbokki jeongol</i>.
-Yes.

867
00:34:49,887 --> 00:34:50,888
ONLY 8 MINUTES AND A HALF LEFT

868
00:34:50,955 --> 00:34:51,956
You should add the <i>tteok</i>.

869
00:34:52,023 --> 00:34:54,092
-I should.
-You have to throw them in now.

870
00:34:54,158 --> 00:34:56,327
-Eight and a half minutes.
-She puts <i>tteok</i> in!

871
00:34:56,394 --> 00:34:59,063
-That looks so good.
-Eight minutes and thirty seconds.

872
00:34:59,730 --> 00:35:01,566
-She's adding tomato sauce.
-Tomato sauce.

873
00:35:01,632 --> 00:35:03,468
Tomato sauce?

874
00:35:03,534 --> 00:35:06,504
That H brand hot pot place
is famous for their tomato broth.

875
00:35:06,571 --> 00:35:07,872
Is that so?

876
00:35:07,939 --> 00:35:09,807
They have tomato soup hot pot.

877
00:35:09,874 --> 00:35:11,509
I wonder what the soup is like.

878
00:35:11,576 --> 00:35:13,845
-Add fish cake and tomatoes.
-I will.

879
00:35:13,911 --> 00:35:15,313
You need fish cake.

880
00:35:15,379 --> 00:35:18,516
<i>Mala tteokbokki jeongol</i> with tomatoes.

881
00:35:19,083 --> 00:35:20,551
-What's the enoki for?
-Enoki.

882
00:35:20,785 --> 00:35:23,754
AFTER CHOPPING ENOKI…

883
00:35:23,821 --> 00:35:25,022
What's he doing?

884
00:35:25,089 --> 00:35:26,924
What will he do with the mushroom?

885
00:35:26,991 --> 00:35:28,426
I can't imagine what he'll do.

886
00:35:28,493 --> 00:35:29,494
SALT

887
00:35:30,161 --> 00:35:31,362
SALT

888
00:35:34,232 --> 00:35:35,600
He must have frozen shoulders.

889
00:35:35,666 --> 00:35:37,902
-He's trying to copy someone.
-The angle was wrong.

890
00:35:38,769 --> 00:35:39,770
What are you making?

891
00:35:39,837 --> 00:35:41,105
I'm cooking the enoki down.

892
00:35:41,172 --> 00:35:44,375
-You'll cook it down with a lid over it?
-He's basically boiling it.

893
00:35:44,909 --> 00:35:45,910
NEXT, SHRIMP!

894
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:47,512
-Shrimp?
-He's using shrimp too?

895
00:35:47,578 --> 00:35:48,713
She said she likes shrimp.

896
00:35:48,779 --> 00:35:50,081
LOVES SEAFOOD

897
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:52,049
-So I'm using seafood.
-Poong is moving quickly.

898
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:54,986
He's moving quickly like LamborGilli.

899
00:35:55,052 --> 00:35:56,120
ADDS SHRIMP TO THE SAUCE!

900
00:35:56,187 --> 00:35:59,624
-You added both meat and shrimp.
-Yes.

901
00:35:59,690 --> 00:36:02,093
This will go right on top
of the scorched rice.

902
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:03,961
I wonder what the pizza will be like.

903
00:36:04,495 --> 00:36:06,063
-It smells really spicy.
-Yes.

904
00:36:06,130 --> 00:36:07,398
-It is.
-It's spicy.

905
00:36:07,465 --> 00:36:08,499
It's not too spicy.

906
00:36:08,566 --> 00:36:10,801
I guess he's using the mushroom.

907
00:36:11,369 --> 00:36:12,803
A NEW PAN

908
00:36:12,870 --> 00:36:15,406
I've never seen him use so many pans.

909
00:36:15,473 --> 00:36:16,807
He's using four.

910
00:36:16,874 --> 00:36:18,543
-What's that?
-Cheese.

911
00:36:18,609 --> 00:36:20,978
I see. Cheese. I thought it was garlic.

912
00:36:21,712 --> 00:36:23,848
MEANWHILE, WHAT'S EUN-YEONG DOING?

913
00:36:24,115 --> 00:36:25,116
SUGAR

914
00:36:25,683 --> 00:36:30,054
Chef Eun-yeong seems
more relaxed than I expected today.

915
00:36:30,121 --> 00:36:32,056
If this continues,
you may not catch up to him.

916
00:36:32,590 --> 00:36:33,824
POONGRARI RUNS WILD

917
00:36:34,025 --> 00:36:35,593
SWOOSH

918
00:36:35,993 --> 00:36:38,095
THAT'S MY POSE

919
00:36:38,596 --> 00:36:41,098
POONGRARI WITH A BROKEN STEERING WHEEL

920
00:36:41,499 --> 00:36:42,500
HMPH

921
00:36:42,967 --> 00:36:44,502
You've seen the match.

922
00:36:44,569 --> 00:36:46,237
Catching up isn't easy
in a short track match.

923
00:36:46,571 --> 00:36:47,838
ACTING CHEEKY

924
00:36:47,905 --> 00:36:49,507
Wait a second.

925
00:36:49,574 --> 00:36:50,875
You can't afford to do that now.

926
00:36:51,442 --> 00:36:52,977
They only have six minutes left.

927
00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:54,845
Only six minutes remain.

928
00:36:54,912 --> 00:36:57,181
-Time flies, doesn't it?
-Time is flying by.

929
00:36:57,248 --> 00:37:00,418
-I can't believe it's done in 15 minutes.
-You must speed up.

930
00:37:00,484 --> 00:37:02,687
He's making something crazy,
so keep it up, Eun-yeong.

931
00:37:02,753 --> 00:37:03,754
What's he doing?

932
00:37:03,821 --> 00:37:05,890
-It looks good.
-You can tell just by looking at it.

933
00:37:05,957 --> 00:37:06,958
You have to step on it.

934
00:37:07,358 --> 00:37:08,960
STEPPING ON THE ACCELERATOR

935
00:37:09,026 --> 00:37:10,695
-Is that peanut butter?
-What's that?

936
00:37:10,761 --> 00:37:14,398
I'm mixing peanut butter with something
Gil-li bought in Italy, basil oil.

937
00:37:14,465 --> 00:37:16,367
-I see. An item from Italy.
-No way.

938
00:37:16,434 --> 00:37:18,603
-That's Eun-yeong sauce.
-Eun-yeong sauce.

939
00:37:18,669 --> 00:37:20,638
-Her personal creation.
-My personal sauce.

940
00:37:20,705 --> 00:37:22,206
What's that sauce for?

941
00:37:22,273 --> 00:37:25,076
She'll dip the <i>jeongol</i> ingredients
in this.

942
00:37:25,376 --> 00:37:27,011
EUN-YEONG'S SAUCE

943
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:30,281
3 PEANUT BUTTER, 1 BASIL OIL, 2 GARLIC,
1 SUGAR, 1 VINEGAR, 1 SOY SAUCE

944
00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:31,349
It looks good.

945
00:37:31,415 --> 00:37:35,319
<i>She cuts inside,</i>
<i>but LamborGilli charges on the outside.</i>

946
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:37,488
Sung-ju, only five minutes remain.

947
00:37:37,555 --> 00:37:40,157
-Let me run to the kitchen!
-Please report from the kitchen.

948
00:37:40,224 --> 00:37:42,126
They're cooking for LamborGilli!

949
00:37:42,193 --> 00:37:44,562
I wonder what kind of flavors
they have created.

950
00:37:44,629 --> 00:37:46,030
I've been curious about this.

951
00:37:46,097 --> 00:37:48,032
This is the <i>jeongol</i>.

952
00:37:48,599 --> 00:37:49,900
Is her new car

953
00:37:49,967 --> 00:37:52,837
LamborGilli?

954
00:37:54,572 --> 00:37:56,040
-It's salty!
-Too salty?

955
00:37:56,107 --> 00:37:57,742
-It's salty!
-Too salty?

956
00:37:57,808 --> 00:37:59,110
-It's too salty?
-Salty!

957
00:37:59,176 --> 00:38:01,579
-It's an emergency.
-She's serving it with mung bean sprouts.

958
00:38:01,646 --> 00:38:03,948
Try it. Isn't it a bit salty?

959
00:38:04,015 --> 00:38:06,050
-It is.
-See? It's too salty.

960
00:38:06,117 --> 00:38:08,119
-It boiled down a little.
-It was a bit salty!

961
00:38:08,185 --> 00:38:09,186
ADDING HOT WATER

962
00:38:09,253 --> 00:38:11,055
THAT'S GREAT NEWS FOR POONG

963
00:38:11,455 --> 00:38:12,923
HE BRINGS THE BLENDED CUCUMBER…

964
00:38:12,990 --> 00:38:15,493
You're adding the cucumber there?

965
00:38:16,927 --> 00:38:18,195
-What's that?
-Cheese?

966
00:38:18,262 --> 00:38:19,363
Cucumber cheese?

967
00:38:19,430 --> 00:38:20,731
APPETITE-KILLING CHEESE

968
00:38:20,798 --> 00:38:22,767
He's mixing mozzarella with cucumber.

969
00:38:22,833 --> 00:38:24,502
Mozzarella and cucumber?

970
00:38:24,568 --> 00:38:27,371
He's making red and blue with mozzarella.

971
00:38:28,272 --> 00:38:30,207
I've never seen
cucumber cheese in my life.

972
00:38:30,274 --> 00:38:31,909
Be careful.

973
00:38:31,976 --> 00:38:34,712
-Use a strainer.
-No, use a spatula.

974
00:38:35,212 --> 00:38:36,480
HOW WILL IT GO?

975
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:38,049
USING ANOTHER PAN

976
00:38:38,115 --> 00:38:39,517
Be careful.

977
00:38:40,084 --> 00:38:41,118
ARGHHHH!

978
00:38:42,987 --> 00:38:43,988
It's ruined!

979
00:38:44,855 --> 00:38:46,090
IT FOLDED

980
00:38:46,590 --> 00:38:48,059
IT'S AN EMERGENCY

981
00:38:48,626 --> 00:38:49,660
What's wrong with him?

982
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:51,495
USING A SPATULA TO RESUSCITATE IT

983
00:38:51,562 --> 00:38:53,531
I MUST SAVE THIS

984
00:38:53,597 --> 00:38:55,032
Poong is in trouble!

985
00:38:56,967 --> 00:38:58,202
It's all ripped apart!

986
00:38:58,836 --> 00:38:59,837
BROKEN INTO PIECES

987
00:39:00,237 --> 00:39:01,238
MY PIZZA…

988
00:39:01,739 --> 00:39:03,607
IRREVERSIBLE

989
00:39:03,674 --> 00:39:04,775
Turn the heat on.

990
00:39:04,842 --> 00:39:06,911
-Just grill it on high heat.
-Use starch.

991
00:39:06,977 --> 00:39:08,079
Mix eggs with starch.

992
00:39:09,046 --> 00:39:10,648
-Starch.
-Eun-yeong takes the upper hand!

993
00:39:10,715 --> 00:39:13,617
Webtoon Artist Poong
just tripped and fell!

994
00:39:13,684 --> 00:39:15,019
-The heat is too low.
-Raise the heat.

995
00:39:15,086 --> 00:39:16,087
Damn it.

996
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:17,621
BEEN A WHILE SINCE WE HEARD THOSE WORDS

997
00:39:17,688 --> 00:39:19,123
ANYONE SMELL SOMETHING BURNING?

998
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:21,726
-Poong is in a crisis!
-It's burning!

999
00:39:21,792 --> 00:39:23,361
Dang it!

1000
00:39:23,427 --> 00:39:24,962
-That looks burnt too.
-Emergency.

1001
00:39:25,029 --> 00:39:28,332
Is that burnt too? What now? Is this okay?

1002
00:39:28,399 --> 00:39:29,800
Wait, what is that?

1003
00:39:29,867 --> 00:39:32,670
Wait, what is that?

1004
00:39:35,039 --> 00:39:37,074
A HUGE CRISIS

1005
00:39:37,575 --> 00:39:39,410
OH, HEAVENS

1006
00:39:39,810 --> 00:39:41,479
THE BIGGEST EMERGENCY
IN THE 2ND SEASON OF THE SHOW

1007
00:39:41,545 --> 00:39:45,383
-You can make it again.
-Melt the cheese again.

1008
00:39:45,449 --> 00:39:47,017
I can do it.

1009
00:39:47,084 --> 00:39:48,786
I'll make a spurt like Gil-li at the end!

1010
00:39:49,286 --> 00:39:51,222
WHY ARE YOU BRINGING ME INTO THIS?

1011
00:39:51,288 --> 00:39:52,757
I'll make a spurt like Gil-li at the end!

1012
00:39:52,823 --> 00:39:54,158
You have two laps left!

1013
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:55,359
-Don't give up.
-I can't give up.

1014
00:39:55,926 --> 00:39:57,561
-Red pepper powder.
-Here.

1015
00:39:57,628 --> 00:39:59,296
-Do not give up.
-Give up.

1016
00:39:59,797 --> 00:40:01,599
-"Give up."
-Give up?

1017
00:40:01,665 --> 00:40:03,834
-I can't give up.
-Give up.

1018
00:40:03,901 --> 00:40:05,069
Two minutes.

1019
00:40:05,136 --> 00:40:07,438
Poong had been taking the lead,
but Eun-yeong was right behind.

1020
00:40:07,505 --> 00:40:10,341
<i>So when Poong fell,</i>
<i>Eun-yeong passed him and took the lead.</i>

1021
00:40:10,508 --> 00:40:11,876
DICING SCALLION

1022
00:40:11,942 --> 00:40:15,913
EUN-YEONG'S SAUCE:
ADD SCALLIONS TO TASTE

1023
00:40:16,313 --> 00:40:18,149
FINISHES THE SAUCE WITH TIME TO SPARE

1024
00:40:18,716 --> 00:40:19,917
I can't give up!

1025
00:40:20,818 --> 00:40:22,553
I've never seen cucumber cheese before.

1026
00:40:22,620 --> 00:40:24,889
-That color…
-It's the Shrek sauce.

1027
00:40:24,955 --> 00:40:26,791
Geez. Look at that color.

1028
00:40:26,857 --> 00:40:27,958
What now?

1029
00:40:28,025 --> 00:40:29,593
What is that?

1030
00:40:30,094 --> 00:40:31,095
It's a slime monster.

1031
00:40:31,862 --> 00:40:33,798
What kind of cheese is that?

1032
00:40:33,864 --> 00:40:35,132
-Cucumber.
-Cucumber cheese?

1033
00:40:35,199 --> 00:40:36,567
Wait, I have to start plating.

1034
00:40:36,634 --> 00:40:37,635
Damn it.

1035
00:40:37,701 --> 00:40:39,003
Now, Poong.

1036
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,304
DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO

1037
00:40:40,371 --> 00:40:41,539
He almost put the dish on the stove.

1038
00:40:42,039 --> 00:40:44,842
THIS IS RIDICULOUS…

1039
00:40:44,909 --> 00:40:47,311
Will he fail to break the curse?

1040
00:40:47,378 --> 00:40:50,047
You have been on a losing streak
against Eun-yeong.

1041
00:40:50,114 --> 00:40:51,649
You said you'd win today.

1042
00:40:51,715 --> 00:40:52,716
Damn it.

1043
00:40:53,217 --> 00:40:54,418
HE TRIES TO LIFT THE SCORCHED RICE

1044
00:40:54,485 --> 00:40:56,153
-No!
-No!

1045
00:40:56,554 --> 00:40:58,055
RAGGED

1046
00:40:58,122 --> 00:40:59,623
It's completely torn apart!

1047
00:41:00,491 --> 00:41:01,559
IS THAT TOILET PAPER?

1048
00:41:02,126 --> 00:41:04,061
Everything is so real.

1049
00:41:04,562 --> 00:41:06,530
THIS IS THE DISH SHE'S SEEING
AFTER WAITING 10 YEARS

1050
00:41:06,597 --> 00:41:08,799
You said you were just like Gil-li!

1051
00:41:09,033 --> 00:41:11,168
POONG IS BLESSED BY THE VARIETY SHOW GODS

1052
00:41:11,569 --> 00:41:14,872
THE POOP LOACH WAS ALSO FOR A SKATER,
CHA JUN-HWAN

1053
00:41:15,372 --> 00:41:17,575
HE'S BLESSED BY THE DEITY OF ICE

1054
00:41:17,641 --> 00:41:19,510
There's only a minute and a half left.

1055
00:41:19,710 --> 00:41:21,345
HE'S PRACTICALLY A CROW

1056
00:41:21,846 --> 00:41:23,814
CAN HE TURN THE GAME AROUND
IN THE LAST MINUTE?

1057
00:41:23,881 --> 00:41:26,217
It looks like someone trampled on it.

1058
00:41:26,283 --> 00:41:27,818
This isn't pizza!

1059
00:41:29,086 --> 00:41:30,120
I can do this.

1060
00:41:30,187 --> 00:41:31,922
Dab the excess grease. You got this.

1061
00:41:31,989 --> 00:41:34,158
-One minute.
-You can do this, just like Gil-li.

1062
00:41:34,225 --> 00:41:36,794
-You have a minute and four seconds.
-It'll probably get stuck.

1063
00:41:36,861 --> 00:41:38,395
OH, NO!

1064
00:41:38,462 --> 00:41:40,364
-It got stuck.
-It got stuck.

1065
00:41:40,431 --> 00:41:41,665
TREMBLING

1066
00:41:42,666 --> 00:41:43,801
It's stuck.

1067
00:41:43,868 --> 00:41:45,503
BECAME ONE WITH THE KITCHEN TOWEL

1068
00:41:45,569 --> 00:41:46,770
It's stuck.

1069
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:51,141
FINALLY REALIZING THAT HE'S DONE FOR

1070
00:41:52,977 --> 00:41:55,279
DISCARDING ALL OF THE SCORCHED RICE

1071
00:41:55,613 --> 00:41:56,847
LEFT TO DIE…

1072
00:41:57,214 --> 00:41:58,849
BUT YOU'RE 1ST PLACE IN COMEDY

1073
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:00,451
THIS SIDE HAS DIED FROM LAUGHING

1074
00:42:00,751 --> 00:42:01,952
ELECTRIC SHOCK

1075
00:42:02,786 --> 00:42:04,221
He's almost crying.

1076
00:42:05,122 --> 00:42:07,992
PLEASE LET THIS NIGHTMARE END…

1077
00:42:08,058 --> 00:42:09,393
This is insane.

1078
00:42:09,460 --> 00:42:11,896
-He's warming up instant rice.
-What now?

1079
00:42:12,263 --> 00:42:13,931
HE'LL MAKE PIZZA WITHOUT DOUGH

1080
00:42:13,998 --> 00:42:16,500
Eun-yeong, you'll win
as long as you ring the bell.

1081
00:42:16,567 --> 00:42:18,335
Why does he do that whenever he fights me?

1082
00:42:18,402 --> 00:42:21,505
It looks like this round
will end quickly. Poong…

1083
00:42:21,572 --> 00:42:22,573
POURING

1084
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:24,141
I just need to ring the bell.

1085
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:27,545
-Just ring the bell, Eun-yeong.
-Ring the bell, and you win.

1086
00:42:27,878 --> 00:42:29,647
POONG LOOKS DEPRESSED

1087
00:42:30,347 --> 00:42:32,416
JUST PIZZA SAUCE WITHOUT DOUGH…

1088
00:42:32,483 --> 00:42:34,885
Stay down, champ.

1089
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:36,453
URGING HIM TO STAY DOWN

1090
00:42:36,854 --> 00:42:39,323
HE DOESN'T SEEM TO HAVE
ENOUGH ENERGY TO GET UP

1091
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:41,492
You have about 15 seconds left.

1092
00:42:41,559 --> 00:42:43,761
Eun-yeong finishes.

1093
00:42:43,827 --> 00:42:46,030
She finishes with ease.

1094
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:47,698
HOW ABOUT POONG, WHO'S LEFT BEHIND?

1095
00:42:47,765 --> 00:42:49,033
Eun-yeong finishes.

1096
00:42:49,099 --> 00:42:51,268
How is that the national flag?

1097
00:42:51,335 --> 00:42:54,405
Let's find out
what kind of pizza he'll serve.

1098
00:42:54,672 --> 00:42:55,806
HERE, THAT'S CHEESE

1099
00:42:56,774 --> 00:42:58,442
THE WORST PRESENTATION EVER

1100
00:42:59,276 --> 00:43:00,644
Is that really pizza?

1101
00:43:00,711 --> 00:43:03,080
-What is that?
-He's making the <i>Taegeuk</i> mark.

1102
00:43:03,147 --> 00:43:04,882
How is that the <i>Taegeuk</i> mark?

1103
00:43:04,949 --> 00:43:06,317
PLOP

1104
00:43:06,684 --> 00:43:08,419
IT LOOKS ILLEGAL…

1105
00:43:08,986 --> 00:43:11,055
THIS TAEGEUK MARK WILL CAUSE CONTROVERSY

1106
00:43:11,121 --> 00:43:14,224
What did Gil-li do so wrong
to deserve that?

1107
00:43:14,625 --> 00:43:16,193
SHE FAILED TO SKIP ON POONG

1108
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:18,162
-I can do it.
-You can do it.

1109
00:43:18,228 --> 00:43:20,531
Please do understand, everyone.

1110
00:43:20,598 --> 00:43:22,333
-Time's already up…
-What is that?

1111
00:43:22,399 --> 00:43:24,335
…but as the judge, I'll let him continue.

1112
00:43:24,401 --> 00:43:25,736
It's the <i>Taegeuk</i> mark.

1113
00:43:25,803 --> 00:43:27,404
THE MARK LOOKS QUITE FADED

1114
00:43:27,471 --> 00:43:29,373
You only warmed that for 40 seconds.

1115
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:32,443
Lastly, the rice. Poong finishes.

1116
00:43:32,509 --> 00:43:34,178
What about the rice?

1117
00:43:34,244 --> 00:43:36,113
What happened to the scorched rice?

1118
00:43:36,180 --> 00:43:38,315
He couldn't do anything anymore.

1119
00:43:38,382 --> 00:43:40,384
-Is that pizza?
-He needs to serve it as is.

1120
00:43:40,818 --> 00:43:42,920
THE MOST ANTICLIMACTIC DISH EVER

1121
00:43:42,987 --> 00:43:44,421
CHOKING UP

1122
00:43:44,488 --> 00:43:45,923
Can you peel off some scorched rice?

1123
00:43:45,990 --> 00:43:47,091
This is pizza?

1124
00:43:47,157 --> 00:43:48,592
What is this?

1125
00:43:48,659 --> 00:43:49,793
CRY LAUGHING

1126
00:43:53,497 --> 00:43:55,199
WHIMPER

1127
00:43:55,265 --> 00:43:57,167
HNGH

1128
00:43:57,434 --> 00:43:59,269
Poong is usually a good cook.

1129
00:43:59,837 --> 00:44:01,805
-Of all times, he fails today.
-Right?

1130
00:44:01,872 --> 00:44:06,577
And now, both dishes were finished
to fill Gil-li's order.

1131
00:44:06,644 --> 00:44:10,114
-Min-jeong waited a decade for this…
-Yes.

1132
00:44:10,180 --> 00:44:12,549
-…but we're sorry you had to see this.
-We're so sorry.

1133
00:44:12,616 --> 00:44:14,485
Poong isn't usually like this.

1134
00:44:14,551 --> 00:44:16,754
And he started off much smoother.

1135
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:20,190
I think it's a common ground
between the show and short track.

1136
00:44:20,257 --> 00:44:21,258
Yes.

1137
00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:24,161
-A good start doesn't mean it'll go well.
-If you fall, it's over.

1138
00:44:24,228 --> 00:44:26,697
That doesn't guarantee
that you'll finish first.

1139
00:44:26,997 --> 00:44:28,132
UNDERSTANDABLE

1140
00:44:28,198 --> 00:44:30,434
But you never know who'll win.

1141
00:44:31,001 --> 00:44:32,269
You really don't know?

1142
00:44:33,037 --> 00:44:34,571
Anyone can see

1143
00:44:34,638 --> 00:44:37,074
that Chef Eun-yeong has the upper hand.

1144
00:44:37,141 --> 00:44:38,842
Please try her dish first.

1145
00:44:38,909 --> 00:44:43,847
MALA TTEOKBOKKI JEONGOL,
JUST AS LAMBORGILLI LIKES IT

1146
00:44:44,348 --> 00:44:46,583
WITH A SIDE OF EUN-YEONG SAUCE

1147
00:44:47,351 --> 00:44:51,388
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
GIRL, I GOT A NEW CAR TO COME FEED YOU

1148
00:44:51,455 --> 00:44:52,723
Where should I begin?

1149
00:44:52,790 --> 00:44:53,791
How should she eat this?

1150
00:44:53,857 --> 00:44:59,129
First, let it boil for a bit until
the mung bean sprouts and meat cooks.

1151
00:44:59,196 --> 00:45:01,765
Then, pick out whatever topping you like

1152
00:45:01,832 --> 00:45:03,333
-and eat it with the sauce.
-How nice.

1153
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:05,169
Can she win against the hot pot franchise?

1154
00:45:05,235 --> 00:45:07,404
She'll win. It's really good.

1155
00:45:07,471 --> 00:45:09,473
-Should I mix it for you?
-Yes, please.

1156
00:45:10,541 --> 00:45:12,142
HELLO, MUNG BEAN SPROUTS

1157
00:45:12,209 --> 00:45:13,277
There are the sprouts.

1158
00:45:13,343 --> 00:45:14,678
-It looks so good.
-My gosh.

1159
00:45:14,745 --> 00:45:17,314
-I can smell it from here.
-Right.

1160
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:19,516
-It smells like <i>mala</i>.
-Yes.

1161
00:45:19,583 --> 00:45:21,318
The more it boils,
the more I can smell it.

1162
00:45:21,385 --> 00:45:24,254
-Gil-li, please have a bite.
-It looks good.

1163
00:45:24,321 --> 00:45:25,556
She tries a piece of <i>tteok</i>.

1164
00:45:26,023 --> 00:45:27,024
BITE!

1165
00:45:30,794 --> 00:45:32,162
Is it already good?

1166
00:45:32,229 --> 00:45:34,198
-Yes.
-It's already that good?

1167
00:45:34,264 --> 00:45:35,999
I'm sorry, but you chewed like twice.

1168
00:45:36,066 --> 00:45:38,202
-I'm serious.
-Have a better taste please.

1169
00:45:38,702 --> 00:45:40,637
A BITE OF ENOKI

1170
00:45:41,605 --> 00:45:43,207
What's it like?

1171
00:45:43,273 --> 00:45:47,745
-The fancier version of the hot pot place.
-Does it taste that much better?

1172
00:45:47,811 --> 00:45:50,681
-My gosh. It's really good.
-Is it really?

1173
00:45:50,748 --> 00:45:53,050
I've been craving <i>tteokbokki</i> too,

1174
00:45:53,117 --> 00:45:57,187
and it feels like
I'm eating hot pot with <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1175
00:45:57,254 --> 00:45:59,556
How does it compare
to the hot pot place you ran to?

1176
00:45:59,623 --> 00:46:02,526
It's nothing like the kind of broth
you'll find there.

1177
00:46:02,826 --> 00:46:04,528
HIGH PRAISE

1178
00:46:04,595 --> 00:46:06,130
My mouth is watering so much.

1179
00:46:06,196 --> 00:46:08,198
She picks out some meat.

1180
00:46:08,265 --> 00:46:09,566
-The meat.
-That's the highlight.

1181
00:46:09,633 --> 00:46:12,369
-It'll taste better with the sauce.
-The sauce.

1182
00:46:12,436 --> 00:46:13,904
Yes, I'll try the sauce.

1183
00:46:13,971 --> 00:46:16,440
-Dip it in the sauce.
-She gets lots of sauce.

1184
00:46:16,507 --> 00:46:18,075
LOTS OF EUN-YEONG SAUCE

1185
00:46:19,476 --> 00:46:20,477
SLURP

1186
00:46:20,878 --> 00:46:22,212
What's it like?

1187
00:46:23,113 --> 00:46:25,149
ENCHANTED

1188
00:46:25,215 --> 00:46:26,483
It's over.

1189
00:46:26,550 --> 00:46:27,718
It looks so good.

1190
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:29,753
-Wow. It's insane.
-It's insane?

1191
00:46:29,820 --> 00:46:35,225
I was a bit worried
about mixing basil oil into the sauce.

1192
00:46:35,292 --> 00:46:37,427
-But it's good.
-Was it a good move?

1193
00:46:37,494 --> 00:46:39,429
-It was the key move.
-The oil from Italy?

1194
00:46:39,496 --> 00:46:41,431
The basil oil was the kick.

1195
00:46:41,698 --> 00:46:42,966
DIPPING TTEOK IN THE SAUCE

1196
00:46:43,233 --> 00:46:46,103
Gil Ra-im seems to love <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1197
00:46:46,170 --> 00:46:48,105
-Gil Ra-im?
-Gil Ra-im?

1198
00:46:50,307 --> 00:46:51,475
GIL-LI

1199
00:46:51,542 --> 00:46:52,843
GIL RA-IM

1200
00:46:52,910 --> 00:46:55,078
-Gil Ra-im?
-What do you mean, Gil Ra-im?

1201
00:46:55,813 --> 00:46:58,982
SHE'S GIL-LI, NOT GIL RA-IM

1202
00:46:59,750 --> 00:47:02,419
I'm out of it too.

1203
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:04,421
When you go to the hot pot place,

1204
00:47:05,055 --> 00:47:08,358
I always order tomato broth
and the spicy broth,

1205
00:47:08,425 --> 00:47:12,129
and this soup
tastes like a mix of the two.

1206
00:47:12,196 --> 00:47:13,697
It's so good.

1207
00:47:14,064 --> 00:47:15,165
A BIG SMILE

1208
00:47:15,232 --> 00:47:16,800
It's really good.

1209
00:47:17,501 --> 00:47:18,769
MINI TZUYANG IS AT WORK

1210
00:47:18,836 --> 00:47:20,270
An athlete indeed.

1211
00:47:20,571 --> 00:47:21,972
A BIG BITE!

1212
00:47:22,039 --> 00:47:25,309
If you mix the ingredients on the plate,

1213
00:47:25,375 --> 00:47:26,844
will it change the flavor?

1214
00:47:26,910 --> 00:47:29,046
LAMBORGILLI SLAMS ON THE ACCELERATOR!

1215
00:47:29,780 --> 00:47:31,181
No words needed.

1216
00:47:32,783 --> 00:47:34,218
You might finish that.

1217
00:47:34,718 --> 00:47:37,921
-You have to try Poong's dish too.
-The cheese is slowly hardening.

1218
00:47:37,988 --> 00:47:40,891
Do you not intend to eat much of his dish?

1219
00:47:40,958 --> 00:47:42,860
We have to move on.

1220
00:47:42,926 --> 00:47:44,661
Next, Poong's dish.

1221
00:47:45,362 --> 00:47:49,399
PIZZA SHAPED LIKE THE TAEGEUK MARK
FOR KIM GIL-LI, A NATIONAL ATHLETE

1222
00:47:51,168 --> 00:47:54,605
FULL OF TOPPINGS
WITHOUT THE SCORCHED RICE DOUGH

1223
00:47:55,405 --> 00:47:59,376
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
KIM GIL-LI PIZZA

1224
00:47:59,443 --> 00:48:02,145
How should she… He's coming.

1225
00:48:02,212 --> 00:48:03,580
WHAT WILL YOU DO?

1226
00:48:04,147 --> 00:48:06,717
Kim Gil-li Pizza. Will you cut it for her?

1227
00:48:06,783 --> 00:48:08,252
-Cut what?
-What's your plan?

1228
00:48:08,318 --> 00:48:12,522
First, I need to cut this
because the cheese has hardened.

1229
00:48:12,589 --> 00:48:14,691
I have to cut it
because of the cheese anyway.

1230
00:48:14,758 --> 00:48:17,694
What happened to the <i>Taegeuk</i> mark?

1231
00:48:17,761 --> 00:48:19,129
It's in our hearts.

1232
00:48:19,196 --> 00:48:21,565
We always keep the mark in our hearts.

1233
00:48:21,632 --> 00:48:22,633
We can see it everywhere.

1234
00:48:22,699 --> 00:48:24,368
-Right?
-Sure.

1235
00:48:24,935 --> 00:48:28,205
-It's the scooping kind of pizza.
-With a spoon?

1236
00:48:28,272 --> 00:48:29,573
-Thanks.
-It might be good.

1237
00:48:29,640 --> 00:48:31,141
Yes, right. Thank you.

1238
00:48:31,208 --> 00:48:32,509
Well, she'll try it.

1239
00:48:32,576 --> 00:48:34,845
-He made it, so see what it's like.
-Try it with rice.

1240
00:48:34,912 --> 00:48:38,081
Scoop some rice with a spoon,

1241
00:48:38,148 --> 00:48:42,452
then top it and eat it as you like.

1242
00:48:42,519 --> 00:48:46,823
It would've been so nice
if the scorched rice worked. What a shame.

1243
00:48:46,890 --> 00:48:49,626
-You never know.
-The rice looks delicious.

1244
00:48:50,260 --> 00:48:52,596
PILING ON THE TOPPING

1245
00:48:52,663 --> 00:48:54,197
-Some cheese.
-Cheese.

1246
00:48:54,798 --> 00:48:56,266
BREAKS

1247
00:48:57,334 --> 00:48:58,535
Wrap it around.

1248
00:48:59,069 --> 00:49:00,904
-Gil-li will try it.
-It's going in.

1249
00:49:00,971 --> 00:49:01,972
STARTING OFF WITH THE RED CHEESE

1250
00:49:02,539 --> 00:49:03,707
A BIG BITE

1251
00:49:03,774 --> 00:49:05,042
She takes a big bite.

1252
00:49:09,046 --> 00:49:10,280
Wait. Again?

1253
00:49:11,248 --> 00:49:12,249
It must be good.

1254
00:49:13,016 --> 00:49:14,518
-What's wrong?
-What is it?

1255
00:49:14,584 --> 00:49:17,187
-Wait, why? What is it?
-Is it good?

1256
00:49:17,254 --> 00:49:18,689
WILL HIS MAGIC WORK AGAIN?

1257
00:49:20,524 --> 00:49:22,960
-It's awesome.
-She says it's awesome.

1258
00:49:23,827 --> 00:49:24,828
EMERGENCY

1259
00:49:24,895 --> 00:49:26,863
-Wait.
-It's good.

1260
00:49:26,930 --> 00:49:28,332
CHOKING UP

1261
00:49:29,099 --> 00:49:32,102
I, KIM POONG, MAY FALL…

1262
00:49:32,169 --> 00:49:34,404
Hey, we don't know who'll win now.

1263
00:49:34,471 --> 00:49:35,505
…BUT I DO NOT GIVE UP!

1264
00:49:35,572 --> 00:49:37,140
No, this is wrong.

1265
00:49:37,207 --> 00:49:39,676
-You never know.
-What's happening to this show?

1266
00:49:40,344 --> 00:49:41,712
I have no idea.

1267
00:49:41,778 --> 00:49:44,181
Does everything he throws out taste good?
Is that his magic?

1268
00:49:44,247 --> 00:49:45,549
No, I mean…

1269
00:49:45,615 --> 00:49:47,784
this tastes insane
when you eat it with rice.

1270
00:49:48,885 --> 00:49:50,487
Does it taste good with rice?

1271
00:49:50,554 --> 00:49:53,790
-He needed the scorched rice.
-That would've been a win.

1272
00:49:53,857 --> 00:49:56,493
I have a feeling
it'll taste like spicy stir-fried chicken.

1273
00:49:56,560 --> 00:49:59,229
-Yes, it's similar.
-Isn't it similar?

1274
00:49:59,296 --> 00:50:01,565
-Spicy stir-fried chicken with cheese.
-Yes, a little.

1275
00:50:01,631 --> 00:50:04,935
But it mixes with seafood flavor
toward the end.

1276
00:50:05,002 --> 00:50:08,405
<i>-He added shrimp.</i>
<i>-Yes, so it's kind of new.</i>

1277
00:50:08,472 --> 00:50:12,009
-It's like spicy stir-fried chicken.
-Yes, and it goes so well with rice.

1278
00:50:12,075 --> 00:50:14,044
-He had to serve rice with it.
-Yes.

1279
00:50:14,678 --> 00:50:15,679
No way.

1280
00:50:15,746 --> 00:50:17,080
"No way"?

1281
00:50:17,147 --> 00:50:18,949
She didn't say that before.

1282
00:50:19,016 --> 00:50:20,484
She didn't.

1283
00:50:20,550 --> 00:50:23,653
-The cucumber cheese.
-I'm dying to know what that's like.

1284
00:50:23,720 --> 00:50:25,856
It's the blue portion of the <i>Taegeuk</i> mark.

1285
00:50:25,922 --> 00:50:29,059
That's something
chefs can never come up with.

1286
00:50:29,126 --> 00:50:32,229
Cucumber cheese is innovative.

1287
00:50:32,295 --> 00:50:34,097
I've done just about everything,

1288
00:50:34,164 --> 00:50:35,832
but never mixed cheese with cucumber.

1289
00:50:35,899 --> 00:50:38,035
He may be the first guy who has done this.

1290
00:50:38,101 --> 00:50:39,369
Try it with some rice.

1291
00:50:39,436 --> 00:50:40,637
THE WORLD'S FIRST CUCUMBER CHEESE TASTING

1292
00:50:42,205 --> 00:50:43,273
The blue side.

1293
00:50:44,441 --> 00:50:46,009
What does it taste like?

1294
00:50:49,946 --> 00:50:52,149
It tastes like lettuce…

1295
00:50:52,916 --> 00:50:54,151
similar to a lettuce wrap.

1296
00:50:54,217 --> 00:50:56,186
-Are you serious?
-Like a lettuce wrap.

1297
00:50:56,486 --> 00:50:57,487
AMAZED

1298
00:50:58,021 --> 00:50:59,723
SO PROUD

1299
00:50:59,790 --> 00:51:02,793
You didn't serve any lettuce,
but it tastes like a lettuce wrap.

1300
00:51:02,859 --> 00:51:05,228
-Is he a genius?
-He did that intentionally?

1301
00:51:05,295 --> 00:51:06,630
Yes, of course.

1302
00:51:06,963 --> 00:51:08,365
GIGGLE

1303
00:51:08,432 --> 00:51:11,435
-I do everything intentionally.
-It sounds like news to him too.

1304
00:51:11,501 --> 00:51:13,103
-How brazen.
-It's…

1305
00:51:13,170 --> 00:51:15,138
-all so good.
-Did he do a good job?

1306
00:51:15,205 --> 00:51:17,407
-Is it good?
-It's really good.

1307
00:51:17,474 --> 00:51:21,044
It may have been an overwhelming win
if he served it with scorched rice.

1308
00:51:21,111 --> 00:51:23,647
-I'll try another bite.
-She tries some more.

1309
00:51:23,713 --> 00:51:25,749
A piece of enoki on top.

1310
00:51:26,316 --> 00:51:28,118
She takes another bite.

1311
00:51:28,185 --> 00:51:30,654
She tries the dish for the third time.

1312
00:51:30,720 --> 00:51:31,988
-No!
-It must be good.

1313
00:51:32,055 --> 00:51:33,056
-Is it good? It is?
-It must be good.

1314
00:51:33,123 --> 00:51:34,424
SHE'S CERTAIN THAT IT'S GOOD

1315
00:51:34,491 --> 00:51:35,992
-The third bite.
-What's happening?

1316
00:51:36,059 --> 00:51:37,627
That's peculiar.

1317
00:51:37,694 --> 00:51:40,063
The green part tastes like a lettuce wrap.

1318
00:51:40,130 --> 00:51:41,498
-Yes.
-Like a lettuce wrap.

1319
00:51:41,565 --> 00:51:42,599
-My gosh.
-How shocking.

1320
00:51:42,666 --> 00:51:44,901
-Min-jeong, why don't you try some?
-That sounds great.

1321
00:51:44,968 --> 00:51:47,104
First, Eun-yeong's dish.

1322
00:51:49,840 --> 00:51:52,242
-Did you dip it in the sauce?
-It's really good. Not yet.

1323
00:51:52,309 --> 00:51:54,010
-The sauce.
-It's really good.

1324
00:51:54,077 --> 00:51:56,146
She already loves it
even without the sauce.

1325
00:51:56,947 --> 00:51:59,282
ANOTHER BITE
AFTER DIPPING IT IN EUN-YEONG SAUCE

1326
00:52:02,752 --> 00:52:05,455
It tastes fantastic
after dipping it in the sauce.

1327
00:52:05,522 --> 00:52:07,357
It's the basil oil.

1328
00:52:07,424 --> 00:52:08,658
That's the kick.

1329
00:52:08,725 --> 00:52:09,960
It's really good.

1330
00:52:10,994 --> 00:52:13,130
ANOTHER BITE WITH THE SAUCE

1331
00:52:13,930 --> 00:52:14,998
I wonder what it's like.

1332
00:52:15,065 --> 00:52:17,767
I like dishes that give
many different flavors in one bite,

1333
00:52:17,834 --> 00:52:20,937
and this tastes like a Chinese dish
with an Italian touch with the basil.

1334
00:52:21,004 --> 00:52:22,906
The mix of different flavors
tastes wonderful.

1335
00:52:23,406 --> 00:52:25,275
MIN-JEONG LOVES HER DISH TOO

1336
00:52:25,342 --> 00:52:28,078
Are you moving on?
She's now trying Poong's dish.

1337
00:52:28,145 --> 00:52:29,412
Will you go for the lettuce wrap?

1338
00:52:29,479 --> 00:52:31,114
-What?
-You should try it second.

1339
00:52:31,181 --> 00:52:34,184
-Try the original first.
-Try the original, the red one first.

1340
00:52:34,251 --> 00:52:37,821
It's ridiculous that a dish like that
has an "original" flavor to it.

1341
00:52:38,321 --> 00:52:39,756
A PIZZA WITH TRADITION?

1342
00:52:39,823 --> 00:52:41,124
There is an original flavor.

1343
00:52:41,791 --> 00:52:43,360
READY TO TRY THE ORIGINAL FLAVOR

1344
00:52:43,426 --> 00:52:46,296
-Try some enoki too.
-Have some enoki with it.

1345
00:52:49,533 --> 00:52:51,201
-What's it like?
-She's flustered.

1346
00:52:51,268 --> 00:52:52,402
-Is it good?
-What's it like?

1347
00:52:52,469 --> 00:52:56,039
-Is it? Not bad? It doesn't taste bad.
-It's not bad. It's good.

1348
00:52:56,606 --> 00:52:58,441
-Next.
-She said it was like a lettuce wrap.

1349
00:52:58,508 --> 00:53:00,944
It wasn't warmed up thoroughly.

1350
00:53:01,011 --> 00:53:03,747
That one probably has
many different flavors too.

1351
00:53:03,813 --> 00:53:05,815
What's it like with some cheese?

1352
00:53:05,882 --> 00:53:06,917
Can you taste the cucumber?

1353
00:53:06,983 --> 00:53:09,252
-It does taste like a lettuce wrap.
-It does?

1354
00:53:09,319 --> 00:53:10,320
A lettuce wrap?

1355
00:53:10,387 --> 00:53:12,589
-That's so peculiar.
-A lettuce wrap from cucumber?

1356
00:53:12,656 --> 00:53:13,990
He made lettuce with cucumber.

1357
00:53:14,057 --> 00:53:15,392
-Wow.
-That's fascinating.

1358
00:53:15,458 --> 00:53:17,661
Have you tried it, Chef Hyun-suk?

1359
00:53:17,727 --> 00:53:21,064
-I'll go straight for the lettuce wrap.
-Does it really taste like it?

1360
00:53:21,464 --> 00:53:23,266
CHOMP, CHOMP

1361
00:53:23,333 --> 00:53:26,436
CHUCKLE

1362
00:53:26,503 --> 00:53:27,804
Do you taste the lettuce wrap?

1363
00:53:28,505 --> 00:53:30,140
<i>He ground up a raw cucumber,</i>

1364
00:53:30,674 --> 00:53:32,175
<i>so it has that grassy smell.</i>

1365
00:53:32,876 --> 00:53:35,011
So when you eat it with some meat,

1366
00:53:35,078 --> 00:53:36,846
it does have the scent of a lettuce wrap.

1367
00:53:37,214 --> 00:53:39,216
YOU'RE RIGHT

1368
00:53:39,282 --> 00:53:40,850
-Rabbits must love it.
-That's odd.

1369
00:53:40,917 --> 00:53:42,719
We thought Eun-yeong would easily win,

1370
00:53:42,786 --> 00:53:44,588
but the tables are turning.

1371
00:53:44,654 --> 00:53:46,590
-Yes.
-May I try this again?

1372
00:53:46,656 --> 00:53:48,858
-That's all yours. Take your time.
-It's yours.

1373
00:53:48,925 --> 00:53:50,760
-Everything's yours.
-It's mine?

1374
00:53:50,827 --> 00:53:52,729
-She is like Tzuyang.
-I wanted the leftovers.

1375
00:53:53,363 --> 00:53:55,332
TRYING EUN-YEONG'S DISH AGAIN

1376
00:53:55,765 --> 00:53:57,200
She should eat what she craves.

1377
00:53:58,001 --> 00:54:00,237
It has boiled down for a bit,

1378
00:54:00,303 --> 00:54:03,406
so it tastes even better
now that the meat has absorbed the broth.

1379
00:54:03,473 --> 00:54:05,041
It's even better?

1380
00:54:05,108 --> 00:54:08,078
-It gets even better over time.
-Yes, right?

1381
00:54:08,144 --> 00:54:10,880
-And now…
-Time to decide.

1382
00:54:10,947 --> 00:54:12,082
Time to decide.

1383
00:54:12,148 --> 00:54:14,517
<i>Press one for Chef Eun-yeong,</i>

1384
00:54:14,584 --> 00:54:16,886
<i>and two for Webtoon Artist Poong.</i>

1385
00:54:16,953 --> 00:54:18,388
Please press a button.

1386
00:54:19,422 --> 00:54:21,024
-I did.
-You did?

1387
00:54:21,091 --> 00:54:22,626
Will it be Eun-yeong or Poong?

1388
00:54:22,692 --> 00:54:24,361
Let's find out her choice.

1389
00:54:24,427 --> 00:54:26,529
Let's see who Gil-li chose.

1390
00:54:26,596 --> 00:54:29,032
A Dish to Make LamborGilli
Slam on the Accelerator.

1391
00:54:29,099 --> 00:54:32,869
Will Eun-yeong beat Poong once again?

1392
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:35,171
Or will Poong get chosen

1393
00:54:35,238 --> 00:54:37,374
after many ups and downs?

1394
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:39,442
Who will receive Gil-li's star?

1395
00:54:39,509 --> 00:54:41,211
Who will it be?

1396
00:54:41,278 --> 00:54:43,680
Show us the winner!

1397
00:54:43,747 --> 00:54:45,081
PARK EUN-YEONG WINS

1398
00:54:45,148 --> 00:54:46,283
GIRL, I GOT A NEW CAR
TO COME FEED YOU WINS

1399
00:54:46,349 --> 00:54:47,484
Eun-yeong wins.

1400
00:54:47,550 --> 00:54:48,652
-So close.
-It was.

1401
00:54:48,718 --> 00:54:51,021
-I mean it.
-There was no twist.

1402
00:54:51,087 --> 00:54:54,758
This means Eun-yeong has won
all five rounds against him.

1403
00:54:55,358 --> 00:54:58,695
Chef Poong's dish…

1404
00:54:58,762 --> 00:55:02,065
was something I was hoping to eat.

1405
00:55:02,832 --> 00:55:04,634
-However…
-However?

1406
00:55:04,701 --> 00:55:06,636
…that is, if he had served scorched rice…

1407
00:55:06,703 --> 00:55:11,308
-So close.
-…then he might have won.

1408
00:55:11,374 --> 00:55:13,610
You wouldn't have considered it
if you hadn't seen him make it.

1409
00:55:13,677 --> 00:55:18,214
-It was a shame that he couldn't serve it.
-He tried to serve it, but he couldn't.

1410
00:55:18,615 --> 00:55:21,151
DEEP REGRETS

1411
00:55:21,217 --> 00:55:23,653
Also, I tried her dish
once again at the last minute,

1412
00:55:23,720 --> 00:55:25,455
and it was very delicious.

1413
00:55:25,522 --> 00:55:27,590
-It was overall well put together.
-Yes.

1414
00:55:27,657 --> 00:55:30,927
Gil-li will put a star on Chef Eun-yeong.

1415
00:55:31,494 --> 00:55:33,296
And the special present too.

1416
00:55:34,064 --> 00:55:36,299
SHE GETS A STAR AND A PRESENT

1417
00:55:36,366 --> 00:55:37,901
Please write down Eun-yeong's name…

1418
00:55:37,967 --> 00:55:39,903
-I almost forgot about this.
-…and present it to her.

1419
00:55:39,969 --> 00:55:41,271
HANDWRITTEN BY GIL-LI

1420
00:55:41,338 --> 00:55:44,741
Please give the kit to Eun-yeong.

1421
00:55:44,808 --> 00:55:46,643
Congratulations!

1422
00:55:46,710 --> 00:55:47,977
CONGRATULATIONS

1423
00:55:48,778 --> 00:55:50,947
<i>Let's take ten and come back.</i>

1424
00:55:51,014 --> 00:55:52,015
SLURP

1425
00:55:52,515 --> 00:55:53,616
SLURP

1426
00:55:53,683 --> 00:55:54,718
Gosh. No way.

1427
00:55:55,618 --> 00:55:56,619
YUM

1428
00:55:56,686 --> 00:55:57,987
It's so good.

1429
00:55:58,054 --> 00:55:59,322
THEY REFUSED TO TAKE A BREAK

1430
00:55:59,956 --> 00:56:01,825
MINI TZUYANG IS BUSY EATING TOO

1431
00:56:02,392 --> 00:56:03,560
YUM

1432
00:56:05,261 --> 00:56:07,764
What do you think about Chef Poong's dish?

1433
00:56:07,831 --> 00:56:09,499
If he had served it with scorched rice…

1434
00:56:09,566 --> 00:56:11,401
-He would've won?
-Seriously.

1435
00:56:11,968 --> 00:56:14,003
CONTINUES TO VACUUM POONG'S DISH

1436
00:56:15,105 --> 00:56:16,272
A BIG BITE

1437
00:56:17,073 --> 00:56:18,942
Don't forget
you'll have to eat your dishes too.

1438
00:56:19,008 --> 00:56:21,678
Yes, but this is so good. And it's so new.

1439
00:56:22,245 --> 00:56:24,647
This is crazy. I finished it.

1440
00:56:25,281 --> 00:56:27,016
How did they do this in 15 minutes?

1441
00:56:27,083 --> 00:56:28,451
So crazy.

1442
00:56:28,518 --> 00:56:30,453
AND THEY KEPT EATING THROUGHOUT THE BREAK

1443
00:56:30,520 --> 00:56:34,557
<i>The next cook-off will be played</i>
<i>with ingredients from Min-jeong's fridge.</i>

1444
00:56:34,624 --> 00:56:37,694
<i>The man who led the glory days</i>
<i>of</i> Chef & My Fridge <i>a decade ago,</i>

1445
00:56:37,761 --> 00:56:38,995
Chef Choi Hyun-suk,

1446
00:56:39,062 --> 00:56:42,532
<i>is up against the man who set fire</i>
<i>on the new heyday of the show,</i>

1447
00:56:42,599 --> 00:56:44,968
Chef Son Jong-won.

1448
00:56:45,034 --> 00:56:48,338
And Min-jeong had been
planning her appearance on the show

1449
00:56:48,405 --> 00:56:51,007
-for the last decade.
-My gosh.

1450
00:56:51,074 --> 00:56:52,475
Do you approve of this match?

1451
00:56:52,542 --> 00:56:54,310
It's a huge honor.

1452
00:56:54,377 --> 00:56:55,912
AN HONORABLE MATCH

1453
00:56:55,979 --> 00:56:57,213
Yes, without Poong in the picture.

1454
00:56:58,581 --> 00:57:00,450
Oh, Chef Jong-won

1455
00:57:00,517 --> 00:57:03,186
-had something to say to Min-jeong.
-Yes?

1456
00:57:03,253 --> 00:57:04,921
It's probably not just me.

1457
00:57:04,988 --> 00:57:08,091
You lifted the spirits of everyone
in the country through your races.

1458
00:57:08,158 --> 00:57:10,493
-So I wanted to cook for you.
-I see.

1459
00:57:10,560 --> 00:57:11,795
Thank you.

1460
00:57:11,861 --> 00:57:13,096
Thank you.

1461
00:57:13,163 --> 00:57:14,964
-He won.
-He won.

1462
00:57:15,031 --> 00:57:16,065
HOW TOUCHING

1463
00:57:16,132 --> 00:57:20,470
-He just passed Hyun-suk on the outside.
-That's right.

1464
00:57:20,537 --> 00:57:22,539
Is there anything
you'd like to say to her?

1465
00:57:23,473 --> 00:57:26,676
There's something
I would like to share with Min-jeong.

1466
00:57:26,910 --> 00:57:28,244
CURIOUS

1467
00:57:28,311 --> 00:57:30,380
The entire nation…

1468
00:57:30,447 --> 00:57:31,881
What did you say again?

1469
00:57:32,315 --> 00:57:33,516
FAILED TO COPY HIS LINES

1470
00:57:33,583 --> 00:57:37,287
We were all encouraged
by the races you have shown us,

1471
00:57:37,353 --> 00:57:39,189
so I wanted to cook for you too.

1472
00:57:39,255 --> 00:57:40,523
Was that about it?

1473
00:57:42,091 --> 00:57:45,228
Min-jeong, you have waited

1474
00:57:45,295 --> 00:57:48,731
over ten years to be on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1475
00:57:48,798 --> 00:57:49,799
But I have been

1476
00:57:50,467 --> 00:57:52,435
waiting to cook for you

1477
00:57:52,502 --> 00:57:54,704
for the last 55 years.

1478
00:57:55,772 --> 00:57:57,140
He waited a long time.

1479
00:57:57,207 --> 00:57:58,608
You say the most random stuff now.

1480
00:57:58,675 --> 00:58:00,910
-Come on.
-He seems anxious.

1481
00:58:00,977 --> 00:58:02,812
FELT ANXIOUS AND MADE AN AWFUL MOVE

1482
00:58:02,879 --> 00:58:05,548
You waited 55 years to cook for Min-jeong?

1483
00:58:05,615 --> 00:58:07,383
I can't win against that.

1484
00:58:07,450 --> 00:58:10,353
-It's half a century.
-Hyun-suk sounds desperate.

1485
00:58:11,287 --> 00:58:13,122
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS:
FIVE-RINGS PASTA, TRUFFLE OIL, BALSAMIC

1486
00:58:13,189 --> 00:58:15,358
INSTANT COFFEE, FRESH CREAM, CREAM CHEESE,
COCOA, STRIP LOIN, SWEET BUN, ARUGULA

1487
00:58:15,425 --> 00:58:18,127
The name of the dish I'll make today is

1488
00:58:18,194 --> 00:58:19,996
Legendary Choi's.

1489
00:58:21,831 --> 00:58:23,199
-Legendary Choi's.
-Legendary Choi's.

1490
00:58:23,266 --> 00:58:25,935
The legendary Choi will make her choice

1491
00:58:26,002 --> 00:58:28,304
and pick this legendary Choi's…

1492
00:58:28,371 --> 00:58:29,639
-Dish?
-Food…

1493
00:58:30,807 --> 00:58:32,175
THE LEGENDARY CHOI SEEMS TO LIKE IT

1494
00:58:32,242 --> 00:58:34,143
What's the dish like?

1495
00:58:34,210 --> 00:58:36,479
She recently played in Italy

1496
00:58:36,546 --> 00:58:38,147
and brought back lots of ingredients.

1497
00:58:38,214 --> 00:58:39,816
I'll use the five-rings pasta,

1498
00:58:39,883 --> 00:58:41,484
but I'll also make ravioli

1499
00:58:41,551 --> 00:58:43,419
and serve it with truffle cream sauce.

1500
00:58:43,486 --> 00:58:46,189
She also wanted a dessert, so I'll make
the most famous Italian dessert,

1501
00:58:46,256 --> 00:58:49,459
-tiramisu, and serve it together.
-Will you have enough time?

1502
00:58:49,526 --> 00:58:51,995
Of course, I feel like I'll probably fall.

1503
00:58:52,061 --> 00:58:53,196
But I will

1504
00:58:53,263 --> 00:58:56,399
fight against myself
and complete these dishes.

1505
00:58:56,466 --> 00:58:57,467
Gosh.

1506
00:58:57,534 --> 00:59:00,069
-So you'll make ravioli and tiramisu?
-Yes.

1507
00:59:00,136 --> 00:59:02,572
-That sounds amazing.
-Let's look forward to it.

1508
00:59:03,406 --> 00:59:05,475
CHEF JONG-WON'S INGREDIENTS:
PASTA RINGS, TRUFFLE MAYO, TRUFFLE OIL,

1509
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:07,577
GRANA PADANO, RAGÚ SAUCE,
SIRLOIN, CANNED HAM, SWEET BUN, AND MORE

1510
00:59:07,644 --> 00:59:10,446
Up against Hyun-suk is Chef Jong-won.
What are you making?

1511
00:59:10,513 --> 00:59:13,750
I prepared three different dishes.

1512
00:59:13,816 --> 00:59:17,820
First, I'll use Korean beef
and make carpaccio as an appetizer.

1513
00:59:17,887 --> 00:59:20,323
Next, I'll make soup called minestrone

1514
00:59:20,390 --> 00:59:22,725
using the five-rings pasta.

1515
00:59:22,792 --> 00:59:23,793
Lastly, for dessert,

1516
00:59:23,860 --> 00:59:26,529
I want to make you something
called a baked Alaska.

1517
00:59:26,596 --> 00:59:28,831
It's a dessert made with meringue.

1518
00:59:28,898 --> 00:59:32,068
It's hot on the outside
and cold on the inside.

1519
00:59:32,135 --> 00:59:34,103
You always train hard in the cold,

1520
00:59:34,170 --> 00:59:35,872
but I wanted to keep your heart warm.

1521
00:59:37,874 --> 00:59:39,375
A LINE WORTHY OF A GOLD MEDAL

1522
00:59:39,442 --> 00:59:41,444
-That was so touching.
-Aw.

1523
00:59:41,511 --> 00:59:42,912
So what's it called?

1524
00:59:42,979 --> 00:59:46,683
She won a total of seven medals,
yet she said it humbly and casually,

1525
00:59:46,749 --> 00:59:48,217
which moved me a lot.

1526
00:59:48,284 --> 00:59:49,452
So I named the dish like this.

1527
00:59:49,519 --> 00:59:52,255
What Did Min-jeong Say
After Winning 7 Medal-ringues?

1528
00:59:54,490 --> 00:59:56,960
-That sounds amazing.
-Wow.

1529
00:59:57,026 --> 00:59:58,661
After Winning 7 Medal-ringues?

1530
00:59:58,728 --> 01:00:00,663
Both chefs sound desperate.

1531
01:00:00,730 --> 01:00:04,801
This will be the dish to celebrate
the Legendary Athlete's Last Dance.

1532
01:00:04,867 --> 01:00:06,736
They look serious
like two competing athletes

1533
01:00:06,803 --> 01:00:08,571
as they stand before the counter.

1534
01:00:08,638 --> 01:00:11,474
Today, he's here to dance
with his knife for Min-jeong.

1535
01:00:11,541 --> 01:00:14,544
The legendary bluff, Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

1536
01:00:14,611 --> 01:00:17,246
He's here to melt
Ice Princess Min-jeong's heart.

1537
01:00:17,313 --> 01:00:20,850
The legendary good vibes,
Chef Son Jong-won.

1538
01:00:20,917 --> 01:00:23,453
Which one of them will take
the legendary athlete's star?

1539
01:00:23,519 --> 01:00:26,456
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1540
01:00:27,123 --> 01:00:29,993
THE 15-MINUTE LONG DISTANCE RACE
BEGINS SLOWLY!

1541
01:00:30,259 --> 01:00:31,494
BEGINS BY MAKING CARPACCIO

1542
01:00:31,561 --> 01:00:33,563
You're cooking for Min-jeong today.

1543
01:00:34,163 --> 01:00:35,965
-Truffle oil.
-What's he doing?

1544
01:00:36,032 --> 01:00:37,166
1. SEASON AND SEAR LOIN

1545
01:00:37,233 --> 01:00:41,337
Chef Jong-won
is searing the beef for the carpaccio.

1546
01:00:41,404 --> 01:00:42,405
I love carpaccio.

1547
01:00:42,472 --> 01:00:44,574
It's a beef dish you eat raw
after just searing the outside.

1548
01:00:44,641 --> 01:00:45,908
ITALIAN SEARED BEEF TARTARE

1549
01:00:46,242 --> 01:00:47,577
ONION

1550
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:49,846
2. GRILL ONION UNTIL CHARRED

1551
01:00:49,912 --> 01:00:51,247
Sugar?

1552
01:00:51,314 --> 01:00:52,482
BEGINS WITH THE TIRAMISU

1553
01:00:52,548 --> 01:00:54,751
She waited a decade to eat these dishes!

1554
01:00:54,817 --> 01:00:56,986
Tiramisu? Oh, coffee.

1555
01:00:57,053 --> 01:00:58,388
-He's using coffee.
-That coffee.

1556
01:00:58,454 --> 01:01:01,357
He said he'll be making tiramisu,

1557
01:01:01,424 --> 01:01:04,127
so he needs espresso
to soak the sheet at the bottom.

1558
01:01:04,193 --> 01:01:05,695
Does he need that much coffee?

1559
01:01:06,195 --> 01:01:08,197
-He does.
-It must require a lot of coffee.

1560
01:01:09,265 --> 01:01:11,601
It would be wise to keep a nice pace.

1561
01:01:11,668 --> 01:01:12,969
The most foolish kind of person

1562
01:01:13,036 --> 01:01:15,838
is someone who gets caught up
by his own pace and falls.

1563
01:01:16,472 --> 01:01:19,108
HMM… I WONDER WHO HE'S TALKING ABOUT

1564
01:01:19,475 --> 01:01:22,345
-Make sure you pace yourself.
-No one is that stupid.

1565
01:01:22,412 --> 01:01:23,413
-Right?
-Right.

1566
01:01:23,479 --> 01:01:24,580
WRAP WITH PLASTIC

1567
01:01:24,647 --> 01:01:26,482
-Like someone who ruins scorched rice?
-Yes.

1568
01:01:26,549 --> 01:01:28,251
Someone who fails to
replace the pizza dough.

1569
01:01:28,317 --> 01:01:30,486
-Carpaccio…
-What's Jong-won up to?

1570
01:01:30,553 --> 01:01:33,423
He threw it into iced water
to cool it before he slices it.

1571
01:01:34,323 --> 01:01:35,792
He's keeping its shape.

1572
01:01:35,858 --> 01:01:38,327
He has to cool it down
to make thin pieces.

1573
01:01:38,394 --> 01:01:39,529
To make thin pieces.

1574
01:01:39,595 --> 01:01:40,596
HE SUDDENLY PASSES HIM!

1575
01:01:40,663 --> 01:01:41,664
Oh, my.

1576
01:01:42,131 --> 01:01:43,933
GIGGLE

1577
01:01:45,768 --> 01:01:47,804
<i>I have been waiting to cook for you</i>

1578
01:01:47,870 --> 01:01:49,572
<i>for the last 55 years.</i>

1579
01:01:49,639 --> 01:01:51,574
THE PERFORMANCE HE WAITED
55 YEARS TO SHOW!

1580
01:01:52,141 --> 01:01:53,509
Wow!

1581
01:01:54,243 --> 01:01:56,045
INSIDE, OUTSIDE
PASSING AT THE SAME TIME

1582
01:01:56,446 --> 01:01:57,647
HYUN-SUK TAKES THE LEAD!

1583
01:01:57,714 --> 01:01:59,982
Hyun-suk waited 55 years to do this!

1584
01:02:00,383 --> 01:02:02,985
REWARDING HER PASSIONATELY
FOR THE WAIT OF 10 YEARS!

1585
01:02:03,052 --> 01:02:04,220
She's so thrilled.

1586
01:02:04,287 --> 01:02:06,155
I finally got to see him do that.

1587
01:02:06,222 --> 01:02:10,026
She seems quite pleased
as she watches the competition live.

1588
01:02:10,093 --> 01:02:12,361
The race is now in favor of Hyun-suk.

1589
01:02:12,428 --> 01:02:14,731
STIR-FRY EVERYTHING IN OLIVE OIL

1590
01:02:15,098 --> 01:02:17,033
THE ACTUAL SEASONING
BUT THE PERFORMANCE

1591
01:02:17,100 --> 01:02:18,768
MUST LOOK INTENSE!

1592
01:02:19,669 --> 01:02:23,139
3. PREP AND STIR-FRY STRIP LOIN,
ONION, AND ARUGULA

1593
01:02:24,240 --> 01:02:25,508
-Ice cream.
-He grabs ice cream.

1594
01:02:25,575 --> 01:02:26,743
For the dessert?

1595
01:02:27,009 --> 01:02:28,010
INTRIGUED

1596
01:02:28,077 --> 01:02:30,680
The name changes
depending on what's put inside.

1597
01:02:30,747 --> 01:02:33,282
If there's fruit inside,
it's called a baked Hawaii.

1598
01:02:34,283 --> 01:02:37,153
I'll use vanilla ice cream
and strawberries, your favorite,

1599
01:02:37,220 --> 01:02:39,655
-and make a baked Milan.
-Baked Milan.

1600
01:02:40,556 --> 01:02:41,991
ATTEMPTS A PASS WITH HIS DISH-NAMING

1601
01:02:42,058 --> 01:02:43,459
I'll use that trick next time.

1602
01:02:43,526 --> 01:02:45,728
I'll make something like a baked Seoul.

1603
01:02:45,795 --> 01:02:47,730
He needs sheets
to prevent it from falling apart.

1604
01:02:47,797 --> 01:02:50,800
So the name changes
depending on what you put inside.

1605
01:02:50,867 --> 01:02:53,803
So he's using bread on the outside.

1606
01:02:53,870 --> 01:02:56,105
He's making baked Milan.

1607
01:02:57,273 --> 01:02:59,108
So that's how you make it.

1608
01:02:59,175 --> 01:03:01,410
Jong-won puts lots of work into it.

1609
01:03:01,477 --> 01:03:02,745
It looks good.

1610
01:03:02,812 --> 01:03:04,113
He grabs strawberries,

1611
01:03:04,180 --> 01:03:05,815
-Min-jeong's favorite.
-Strawberries.

1612
01:03:05,882 --> 01:03:07,984
Is it similar to that ice cream sandwich,

1613
01:03:08,050 --> 01:03:09,385
the one with soft bread?

1614
01:03:09,952 --> 01:03:12,655
-Yes, it's like that.
-It's like that, right?

1615
01:03:12,722 --> 01:03:14,657
-But there's meringue on it.
-Right. Meringue.

1616
01:03:14,724 --> 01:03:16,058
It looks good.

1617
01:03:16,125 --> 01:03:18,327
He'll probably wrap it with plastic.

1618
01:03:18,394 --> 01:03:19,896
He flipped it over.

1619
01:03:19,962 --> 01:03:20,963
It goes into the freezer.

1620
01:03:21,030 --> 01:03:22,365
INTO THE FREEZER!

1621
01:03:23,099 --> 01:03:24,233
PROTECTING HIS PLACE USING ALL FOURS

1622
01:03:24,300 --> 01:03:25,902
What are you grinding?

1623
01:03:25,968 --> 01:03:27,670
-Fresh pasta.
-He's making pasta dough.

1624
01:03:27,737 --> 01:03:28,738
FRESH PASTA WITH EGGS!

1625
01:03:28,805 --> 01:03:30,606
Right, he said he'll make ravioli.

1626
01:03:30,673 --> 01:03:33,476
You're using her pasta from Italy
and also fresh pasta, right?

1627
01:03:33,543 --> 01:03:34,544
No way.

1628
01:03:34,610 --> 01:03:36,546
-The ravioli dough.
-Does it look okay?

1629
01:03:36,612 --> 01:03:39,215
Hyun-suk is in a hurry,
and he's giving his best too.

1630
01:03:39,282 --> 01:03:40,650
He has waited 55 years for this.

1631
01:03:40,716 --> 01:03:41,851
STIR-FRIED VEGGIES INTO THE BLENDER!

1632
01:03:41,918 --> 01:03:43,152
-He's grinding that?
-The veggies?

1633
01:03:43,219 --> 01:03:44,687
-Grinding?
-To make a paste.

1634
01:03:44,754 --> 01:03:46,989
-I see. He'll make a paste.
-Like cream sauce.

1635
01:03:47,056 --> 01:03:48,224
Grinding it after stir-frying?

1636
01:03:48,291 --> 01:03:50,359
So that he can take it out
soon after the noodles cook.

1637
01:03:50,593 --> 01:03:52,562
HE'S CUTTING TIME TO MAKE IT IN 15 MINUTES

1638
01:03:52,628 --> 01:03:54,764
The filling usually goes in uncooked.

1639
01:03:54,831 --> 01:03:56,332
I GOT NO TIME TO EXPLAIN!

1640
01:03:56,399 --> 01:03:57,533
JUST HOP ON!

1641
01:03:58,034 --> 01:03:59,068
RAVIOLI IS A COMPLICATED DISH

1642
01:03:59,135 --> 01:04:01,304
He has many procedures to take

1643
01:04:01,370 --> 01:04:03,906
-in order to make ravioli.
-He has a lot to do.

1644
01:04:03,973 --> 01:04:06,142
-He must make the pasta too.
-Isn't it too hard?

1645
01:04:06,209 --> 01:04:08,077
RACING AHEAD!

1646
01:04:08,444 --> 01:04:09,979
AMAZED EVERY TIME

1647
01:04:10,513 --> 01:04:13,516
Things that are dumpling-shaped
always take a lot of work and time.

1648
01:04:13,583 --> 01:04:14,951
AS TOUGH AS PASSING ON THE OUTSIDE

1649
01:04:15,017 --> 01:04:17,453
Hyun-suk takes the tough journey.

1650
01:04:17,520 --> 01:04:19,789
But he has waited 55 years,

1651
01:04:19,856 --> 01:04:22,325
so he desperately wants to make
a heartfelt dish for her.

1652
01:04:22,892 --> 01:04:25,962
I bought the pasta
to make things easier for the chefs,

1653
01:04:26,028 --> 01:04:27,997
yet he chose to make fresh pasta.

1654
01:04:28,064 --> 01:04:29,198
I'm really moved.

1655
01:04:29,932 --> 01:04:32,235
-It must require lots of work.
-It does.

1656
01:04:32,301 --> 01:04:35,571
Min-jeong knows
why you're doing this for her.

1657
01:04:36,239 --> 01:04:38,875
JONG-WON BEGINS TO MAKE
HIS HEARTFELT SOUP TOO!

1658
01:04:39,141 --> 01:04:40,610
ONION

1659
01:04:40,810 --> 01:04:42,545
CARROT

1660
01:04:44,714 --> 01:04:46,182
CANNED HAM

1661
01:04:46,549 --> 01:04:48,284
ITALIAN VEGGIE SOUP, MINESTRONE!

1662
01:04:48,351 --> 01:04:51,053
Did you throw in the five-rings pasta?

1663
01:04:51,120 --> 01:04:52,622
-Chef Hyun-suk did.
-He did?

1664
01:04:52,688 --> 01:04:55,024
I think Jong-won will add it
into his veggie soup.

1665
01:04:55,091 --> 01:04:57,393
Shouldn't he throw it in soon?
It'll take a while to cook.

1666
01:04:57,460 --> 01:04:59,629
-It'll take eight minutes.
-Will it in eight?

1667
01:04:59,695 --> 01:05:02,164
Both chefs are using the five-rings pasta.

1668
01:05:02,865 --> 01:05:04,267
He added the pasta.

1669
01:05:04,333 --> 01:05:05,902
-He did.
-Ten minutes left.

1670
01:05:05,968 --> 01:05:08,504
-You only have ten minutes.
-Ten minutes to go.

1671
01:05:08,571 --> 01:05:10,006
There's so little time.

1672
01:05:10,072 --> 01:05:11,774
Can you give them more time?

1673
01:05:11,841 --> 01:05:13,676
No, we can't.

1674
01:05:13,743 --> 01:05:15,678
Just five minutes. No, three?

1675
01:05:15,745 --> 01:05:17,179
No, we can't do that.

1676
01:05:17,246 --> 01:05:19,015
Do you get more time
during short track races?

1677
01:05:19,081 --> 01:05:20,182
-No.
-No, right?

1678
01:05:20,249 --> 01:05:21,884
It's the same thing. This is our match.

1679
01:05:22,118 --> 01:05:24,086
BUT SHORT TRACK RACES
DON'T HAVE TIME LIMITS

1680
01:05:24,153 --> 01:05:25,922
And if they fail, it's game over.

1681
01:05:25,988 --> 01:05:27,356
You've seen Poong.

1682
01:05:27,823 --> 01:05:28,824
BIG-TIME CRIMINAL

1683
01:05:29,692 --> 01:05:32,595
I became the worst example for them.

1684
01:05:32,662 --> 01:05:35,131
If we could, we already would've
given Poong more time.

1685
01:05:35,197 --> 01:05:36,198
TAPPING

1686
01:05:37,900 --> 01:05:39,702
EGG YOLK

1687
01:05:40,102 --> 01:05:42,805
-Cream. Where's the fresh cream?
-What are you looking for?

1688
01:05:42,872 --> 01:05:44,340
Fresh cream.

1689
01:05:45,041 --> 01:05:46,943
FRESH CREAM
CREAM CHEESE

1690
01:05:47,610 --> 01:05:48,744
Where's the sugar?

1691
01:05:48,811 --> 01:05:50,813
What? Sugar? Right there.

1692
01:05:50,880 --> 01:05:51,914
SUGAR

1693
01:05:51,981 --> 01:05:55,251
WHY DOES IT SEEM LIKE
HE'S CONTINUOUSLY SLIPPING?

1694
01:05:55,885 --> 01:05:56,886
What's that?

1695
01:05:56,953 --> 01:05:59,021
-What's that? It's splattering everywhere.
-What's that?

1696
01:05:59,088 --> 01:06:00,690
It's splattering too much.

1697
01:06:00,756 --> 01:06:02,558
-What's that?
-I'm sorry.

1698
01:06:02,625 --> 01:06:04,393
-That was ruined.
-He ruined it.

1699
01:06:04,894 --> 01:06:06,262
OH, IT'S BEEN RUINED

1700
01:06:06,329 --> 01:06:08,164
-Did you ruin it? Why?
-He tossed it.

1701
01:06:08,230 --> 01:06:09,799
The bowl was too shallow.

1702
01:06:09,865 --> 01:06:12,802
-He's making tiramisu.
-There was a mistake in his calculations.

1703
01:06:12,868 --> 01:06:13,936
Just use fresh cream first.

1704
01:06:14,003 --> 01:06:16,172
Was his plan a bit off?

1705
01:06:16,238 --> 01:06:18,040
Will plan B work successfully?

1706
01:06:18,107 --> 01:06:20,443
He has to turn left,
but he just turned right!

1707
01:06:20,509 --> 01:06:22,278
-He's in a crisis.
-It's a crisis!

1708
01:06:22,845 --> 01:06:24,313
6. WHIP FRESH CREAM AND SUGAR

1709
01:06:24,380 --> 01:06:25,781
-One more time.
-It's splattering.

1710
01:06:25,848 --> 01:06:27,850
-He makes meringue.
-That takes a while.

1711
01:06:27,917 --> 01:06:29,418
It does. Do it manually.

1712
01:06:29,485 --> 01:06:31,620
Do it manually. That'll be better.

1713
01:06:31,687 --> 01:06:34,423
Eight minutes left,
and Hyun-suk faces a crisis.

1714
01:06:34,490 --> 01:06:35,491
Oh, no.

1715
01:06:35,558 --> 01:06:38,561
Jong-won is still racing smoothly.

1716
01:06:39,328 --> 01:06:42,064
He's getting ready to make meringue.

1717
01:06:43,366 --> 01:06:45,501
-He's making meringue?
-Jong-won's making meringue?

1718
01:06:45,568 --> 01:06:48,037
That much meringue
will take forever to whip.

1719
01:06:48,104 --> 01:06:50,239
-But he's using a machine.
-What?

1720
01:06:50,306 --> 01:06:52,074
-Cutting-edge technology.
-What?

1721
01:06:52,141 --> 01:06:53,275
Why does he have a machine?

1722
01:06:53,576 --> 01:06:56,846
THE MACHINE-MADE MERINGUE ON THE SHOW!

1723
01:06:57,513 --> 01:06:58,814
HAHAHAHA

1724
01:06:58,881 --> 01:07:02,585
Why doesn't Chef Hyun-suk
have that machine?

1725
01:07:02,651 --> 01:07:05,788
-Jong-won had a machine!
-What is this?

1726
01:07:05,855 --> 01:07:08,691
-Well, he's using a machine, but…
-Don't you have a better one?

1727
01:07:08,758 --> 01:07:10,493
He's using a machine too,

1728
01:07:10,559 --> 01:07:13,396
but that machine is a specialized one

1729
01:07:13,462 --> 01:07:15,631
-while this one is all-purpose.
-That's a good one.

1730
01:07:15,698 --> 01:07:18,267
I see. Is that his personal machine?

1731
01:07:18,334 --> 01:07:20,302
It's not his personal machine.

1732
01:07:20,369 --> 01:07:21,504
-What?
-No?

1733
01:07:21,570 --> 01:07:23,272
-Our team had it.
-Really?

1734
01:07:24,140 --> 01:07:25,241
We've always had it?

1735
01:07:25,307 --> 01:07:28,377
It's a hand-held machine,
but I put it on its stand.

1736
01:07:28,444 --> 01:07:32,081
-I see.
-I guess Hyun-suk didn't know what it was.

1737
01:07:32,148 --> 01:07:33,649
Did he think it was a sewing machine?

1738
01:07:33,783 --> 01:07:34,784
HAHA

1739
01:07:34,850 --> 01:07:36,619
Jong-won knew what it was,

1740
01:07:36,685 --> 01:07:38,988
-but Hyun-suk didn't.
-That could happen.

1741
01:07:39,055 --> 01:07:40,623
What has life done to you?

1742
01:07:40,689 --> 01:07:42,792
That thing wasn't around
when he learned to cook.

1743
01:07:42,858 --> 01:07:45,428
-It wasn't around 55 years ago.
-No.

1744
01:07:45,494 --> 01:07:46,495
HEARTBROKEN

1745
01:07:46,562 --> 01:07:48,330
-Six and a half minutes.
-Six and a half minutes.

1746
01:07:48,831 --> 01:07:52,068
7. ADD CREAM CHEESE, SALT, AND FLOUR
TO THE GROUND STIR-FRIED STRIP LOIN

1747
01:07:52,134 --> 01:07:53,969
The dough is ready.

1748
01:07:54,036 --> 01:07:55,438
You just need to make two.

1749
01:07:56,005 --> 01:07:57,540
-You don't have enough time.
-You don't.

1750
01:07:57,606 --> 01:07:58,674
You have under six minutes.

1751
01:07:58,741 --> 01:08:01,077
-He needs to cook the ravioli now.
-The ravioli.

1752
01:08:01,577 --> 01:08:03,079
HIS HANDS ARE AS FAST
AS A MACHINE!

1753
01:08:03,145 --> 01:08:05,514
-You have to make tiramisu too.
-You got 5 minutes and 40 seconds.

1754
01:08:05,581 --> 01:08:08,484
-Five minutes and thirty seconds.
-Hyun-suk is moving fast.

1755
01:08:08,551 --> 01:08:11,754
And cover the top. That's ravioli.

1756
01:08:11,821 --> 01:08:12,855
8. FILL THE RAVIOLI

1757
01:08:12,922 --> 01:08:14,857
-It's ready.
-He has to cut it now.

1758
01:08:14,924 --> 01:08:18,294
-Yes, he needs to make the shape.
-Yes, make the shape.

1759
01:08:18,360 --> 01:08:20,830
-You have to keep it up!
-Yes, keep it up!

1760
01:08:20,896 --> 01:08:23,065
-Chase after Jong-won!
-Chef Hyun-suk!

1761
01:08:23,132 --> 01:08:24,867
9. BOIL CREAM, TRUFFLE OIL,
BALSAMIC VINEGAR

1762
01:08:25,334 --> 01:08:27,536
IN A HURRY, SO THROWS THE SALT LOW

1763
01:08:30,406 --> 01:08:34,477
Chef Jong-won races smoothly
and seizes his lead on the ice!

1764
01:08:34,543 --> 01:08:36,045
The carpaccio.

1765
01:08:36,112 --> 01:08:37,279
He's slicing the carpaccio.

1766
01:08:37,913 --> 01:08:39,315
Carpaccio.

1767
01:08:39,381 --> 01:08:40,950
It looks awesome.

1768
01:08:41,016 --> 01:08:43,118
-The one in the iced water?
-The strip loin?

1769
01:08:43,185 --> 01:08:46,055
-Is it like <i>tataki</i> in Japanese cuisine?
-Yes.

1770
01:08:46,122 --> 01:08:48,991
Kind of, but it's closer to beef tartare.

1771
01:08:49,658 --> 01:08:50,893
COVER IT WITH PLASTIC AGAIN

1772
01:08:50,960 --> 01:08:53,863
He's slamming on the meat.

1773
01:08:53,929 --> 01:08:57,032
-It looks good.
-Thinning it out will make it tender.

1774
01:08:57,933 --> 01:09:00,369
ITALIAN BEEF TARTARE, CARPACCIO!
TRUFFLE OIL - GROUND PEPPER

1775
01:09:01,370 --> 01:09:02,872
TURNING OVER

1776
01:09:03,305 --> 01:09:07,109
8. COAT WITH TRUFFLE OIL, GROUND PEPPER,
AND TRUFFLE MAYONNAISE

1777
01:09:07,176 --> 01:09:08,511
He's rolling it up.

1778
01:09:09,178 --> 01:09:10,946
-He is?
-What did he put inside?

1779
01:09:11,814 --> 01:09:14,416
-Truffle mayo.
-Truffle mayo.

1780
01:09:14,483 --> 01:09:16,285
-Wow.
-Truffle mayo?

1781
01:09:16,352 --> 01:09:17,653
And truffle olive oil.

1782
01:09:17,720 --> 01:09:19,755
-Truffle oil.
-He's giving it many layers.

1783
01:09:19,822 --> 01:09:21,790
-Five minutes, Jung-hwan!
-Yes?

1784
01:09:21,857 --> 01:09:24,293
-They only have five more minutes?
-Please go to the kitchen.

1785
01:09:24,360 --> 01:09:25,761
Hurry and report from the kitchen.

1786
01:09:25,828 --> 01:09:27,796
Will they capture Min-jeong's appetite

1787
01:09:27,863 --> 01:09:29,598
-after a decade of waiting?
-With napa cabbage?

1788
01:09:29,665 --> 01:09:32,034
He's wrapping the carpaccio
with napa cabbage.

1789
01:09:33,035 --> 01:09:34,270
He's adding more meat?

1790
01:09:34,336 --> 01:09:36,772
-It smells like truffles.
-Is it a flower?

1791
01:09:36,839 --> 01:09:38,607
-Is that a rose?
-Could it be a flower?

1792
01:09:39,408 --> 01:09:41,777
-No way!
-That's so pretty.

1793
01:09:41,844 --> 01:09:43,045
It's a rose!

1794
01:09:43,112 --> 01:09:44,813
A ROSE, THE QUEEN OF FLOWERS

1795
01:09:45,514 --> 01:09:47,049
-It's a flower!
-That's amazing.

1796
01:09:47,116 --> 01:09:48,450
For her last dance.

1797
01:09:48,517 --> 01:09:51,320
-I didn't realize.
-A flower for her.

1798
01:09:51,387 --> 01:09:52,588
How touching.

1799
01:09:52,655 --> 01:09:55,758
-That's so pretty.
-What a moving moment.

1800
01:09:55,824 --> 01:09:57,593
Why is Hyun-suk looking around?

1801
01:09:57,660 --> 01:09:58,994
He's cooking ravioli now.

1802
01:09:59,061 --> 01:10:00,829
-You're using that bread?
-It's okay.

1803
01:10:00,896 --> 01:10:02,631
He's using sweet buns to make tiramisu.

1804
01:10:02,698 --> 01:10:04,133
Is this tiramisu?

1805
01:10:04,200 --> 01:10:05,901
That coffee looks too strong.

1806
01:10:05,968 --> 01:10:08,971
-What now? Four minutes left.
-He drains some coffee.

1807
01:10:09,038 --> 01:10:10,706
-He needs to let it get wet.
-The cream.

1808
01:10:10,773 --> 01:10:12,508
-What do you need?
-Did you finish the cream?

1809
01:10:12,575 --> 01:10:14,243
-Did you finish it?
-The cream.

1810
01:10:14,310 --> 01:10:16,245
-It turned into cream!
-It's creamy.

1811
01:10:16,312 --> 01:10:17,580
-All good.
-He made the cream.

1812
01:10:17,646 --> 01:10:20,182
He's making the dessert, tiramisu.

1813
01:10:21,917 --> 01:10:24,186
THINLY SLICED GRANA PADANO

1814
01:10:24,253 --> 01:10:26,322
Jong-won is practically making art.

1815
01:10:26,388 --> 01:10:27,823
9. ADD GRANA PADANO AND ARUGULA

1816
01:10:27,890 --> 01:10:29,959
He made a rose out of carpaccio.

1817
01:10:30,025 --> 01:10:31,260
"You Are Like a Rose."

1818
01:10:31,327 --> 01:10:32,962
Yes, Min-jeong, you're a rose.

1819
01:10:33,028 --> 01:10:34,463
A SINGLE ROSE

1820
01:10:34,530 --> 01:10:36,398
-It looks nice.
-It does.

1821
01:10:36,465 --> 01:10:38,500
-That's so cool.
-I think it's done.

1822
01:10:38,567 --> 01:10:40,736
Hyun-suk finished making his dessert.

1823
01:10:40,803 --> 01:10:43,439
It looks really good.
Is that cocoa powder?

1824
01:10:44,707 --> 01:10:46,208
INTO THE FREEZER

1825
01:10:46,275 --> 01:10:48,577
-He has to cool it down.
-It should go into the freezer.

1826
01:10:48,644 --> 01:10:50,613
-There it is.
-Baked Milan?

1827
01:10:51,513 --> 01:10:53,282
Three minutes to go.

1828
01:10:53,349 --> 01:10:55,017
-Baked Milan.
-The dessert.

1829
01:10:55,084 --> 01:10:56,452
I hope it slips out.

1830
01:10:56,518 --> 01:10:58,520
I hope it does. No!

1831
01:10:58,587 --> 01:10:59,955
THE STRAWBERRIES CAME OFF!

1832
01:11:00,356 --> 01:11:02,124
IT'S AN EMERGENCY

1833
01:11:02,191 --> 01:11:03,325
Oh, no!

1834
01:11:03,659 --> 01:11:04,827
COVER IT BACK UP FOR NOW

1835
01:11:04,893 --> 01:11:07,062
It doesn't look good!
Jong-won faces a crisis!

1836
01:11:07,129 --> 01:11:09,465
He's about to slip on the ice!

1837
01:11:09,531 --> 01:11:11,967
-Jong-won's crisis!
-He's melting it a little.

1838
01:11:12,034 --> 01:11:13,535
This is a chance for Hyun-suk!

1839
01:11:14,003 --> 01:11:15,471
SUCCESS!

1840
01:11:15,537 --> 01:11:16,739
It came out!

1841
01:11:16,972 --> 01:11:18,474
HE HELD OUT THROUGH THE CRISIS!

1842
01:11:18,540 --> 01:11:19,808
-He got it out!
-He did.

1843
01:11:19,875 --> 01:11:21,310
He overcomes the crisis!

1844
01:11:21,377 --> 01:11:22,911
Jong-won overcomes the crisis.

1845
01:11:22,978 --> 01:11:25,247
The five-rings pasta is ready.

1846
01:11:25,314 --> 01:11:26,682
The pasta from Italy.

1847
01:11:26,749 --> 01:11:28,083
12. MIX PASTA IN TRUFFLE CREAM SAUCE

1848
01:11:28,651 --> 01:11:30,119
-Salt!
-Yes.

1849
01:11:30,185 --> 01:11:31,520
He's busy, but he still does it.

1850
01:11:31,787 --> 01:11:34,056
HE MAY BE BUSY,
BUT HE MUST DO WHAT HE MUST

1851
01:11:34,823 --> 01:11:35,824
-One more time!
-Yes!

1852
01:11:35,891 --> 01:11:37,126
THE LAST SALT OF THE LEGENDARY BLUFF!

1853
01:11:37,726 --> 01:11:39,161
FIVE-FLAGS PASTA IS DONE!

1854
01:11:39,228 --> 01:11:41,196
There are only 2,026 boxes of that pasta.

1855
01:11:41,263 --> 01:11:42,998
Hyun-suk begins to plate his dishes.

1856
01:11:43,065 --> 01:11:44,066
Hyun-suk.

1857
01:11:44,133 --> 01:11:46,235
Chef Hyun-suk is unfazed.

1858
01:11:46,302 --> 01:11:48,537
He's unfazed even in the face of crisis.

1859
01:11:48,604 --> 01:11:49,605
The ravioli.

1860
01:11:49,672 --> 01:11:50,939
It's not cooked!

1861
01:11:51,006 --> 01:11:52,141
-It's not?
-It's fully cooked.

1862
01:11:52,207 --> 01:11:53,709
-It is?
-It's okay, it's fresh pasta.

1863
01:11:53,776 --> 01:11:54,777
That'll cook fast.

1864
01:11:54,843 --> 01:11:56,245
Two minutes left.

1865
01:11:56,478 --> 01:11:57,613
JONG-WON'S MERINGUE IS READY

1866
01:11:57,680 --> 01:11:59,114
He scoops up the meringue.

1867
01:11:59,181 --> 01:12:00,416
It's a bit runny.

1868
01:12:01,684 --> 01:12:02,818
Will it be okay?

1869
01:12:02,885 --> 01:12:03,986
AMAZED

1870
01:12:04,053 --> 01:12:06,121
That's how he's using the meringue!

1871
01:12:06,789 --> 01:12:07,790
Hey.

1872
01:12:07,856 --> 01:12:09,458
He's coating this with meringue!

1873
01:12:09,525 --> 01:12:12,461
Baked Milan!

1874
01:12:12,528 --> 01:12:13,529
That's pretty.

1875
01:12:13,595 --> 01:12:15,864
He's coating it like a castle.
It's his dessert.

1876
01:12:15,931 --> 01:12:18,767
Both chefs
are doing their best in this race

1877
01:12:18,834 --> 01:12:21,470
for Min-jeong, who waited ten years
for this opportunity.

1878
01:12:21,537 --> 01:12:24,573
Hyun-suk will serve freshly made pasta

1879
01:12:24,640 --> 01:12:27,242
with the pasta she brought from Italy.

1880
01:12:27,309 --> 01:12:30,312
-His pasta is ready.
-It is.

1881
01:12:30,379 --> 01:12:32,181
-You have one minute left.
-One minute!

1882
01:12:32,247 --> 01:12:34,950
-You have under a minute.
-Cheese.

1883
01:12:35,017 --> 01:12:37,219
This is your last spurt!

1884
01:12:37,286 --> 01:12:39,088
Who'll pass the goal line first?

1885
01:12:39,154 --> 01:12:40,589
The last two laps!

1886
01:12:40,656 --> 01:12:41,990
Ring the bell!

1887
01:12:42,057 --> 01:12:43,892
JONG-WON GOES TO PLATE THE DISH TOO

1888
01:12:43,959 --> 01:12:46,028
Is Hyun-suk done? He is.

1889
01:12:46,095 --> 01:12:48,731
-Hyun-suk is done.
-Chef Hyun-suk is finished.

1890
01:12:48,797 --> 01:12:50,332
-Is that the tiramisu?
-Yes.

1891
01:12:50,399 --> 01:12:53,302
You have lots of time, Jong-won.

1892
01:12:53,369 --> 01:12:56,872
He put the five-rings pasta
into this soup.

1893
01:12:56,939 --> 01:12:58,273
-It's in there?
-Yes.

1894
01:12:58,340 --> 01:12:59,575
Jong-won is also finishing up.

1895
01:12:59,641 --> 01:13:00,642
MINESTRONE FINISHED

1896
01:13:00,709 --> 01:13:03,712
-Thirty seconds left. The final lap!
-The final lap!

1897
01:13:03,779 --> 01:13:05,714
-Jong-won keeps racing.
-Yes.

1898
01:13:05,781 --> 01:13:08,484
You need to cut inside!

1899
01:13:08,550 --> 01:13:10,285
ALL HE NEEDS TO DO NOW
IS TOAST THE MERINGUE

1900
01:13:10,853 --> 01:13:13,255
-You have twenty seconds left!
-Twenty seconds.

1901
01:13:13,322 --> 01:13:15,824
Push your foot into the goal line!

1902
01:13:15,891 --> 01:13:17,459
-The last spurt.
-The last one.

1903
01:13:17,526 --> 01:13:18,861
-Ten seconds!
-Ten.

1904
01:13:18,927 --> 01:13:20,863
-The torch.
-Nine. Eight.

1905
01:13:20,929 --> 01:13:22,831
-Seven. Six.
-Seven. Six.

1906
01:13:22,898 --> 01:13:24,032
-Five.
-Five.

1907
01:13:24,099 --> 01:13:26,135
11. ROAST MERINGUE WITH A TORCH

1908
01:13:26,201 --> 01:13:28,470
-Two. One.
-Two. One.

1909
01:13:28,537 --> 01:13:29,605
Time's up.

1910
01:13:29,805 --> 01:13:31,673
JONG-WON FINISHES HIS DISH

1911
01:13:31,740 --> 01:13:33,609
Both of them finished in time.

1912
01:13:35,744 --> 01:13:36,745
THE HIGHEST QUALITY YET

1913
01:13:36,812 --> 01:13:38,547
They made all these in 15 minutes.

1914
01:13:38,714 --> 01:13:39,715
HAHAHAHAHAHA

1915
01:13:39,782 --> 01:13:40,783
These look so good.

1916
01:13:40,849 --> 01:13:41,850
This is insane.

1917
01:13:41,917 --> 01:13:43,318
How did they do this in 15 minutes?

1918
01:13:43,952 --> 01:13:45,954
TO THE QUEEN OF THE ICE!

1919
01:13:46,021 --> 01:13:47,022
They're incredible.

1920
01:13:48,957 --> 01:13:51,193
-It makes no sense.
-No way.

1921
01:13:51,260 --> 01:13:54,797
And the dishes for Min-jeong are served.

1922
01:13:54,863 --> 01:13:57,433
-Are you pleased?
-Yes, I really am.

1923
01:13:57,499 --> 01:13:59,268
I saw everything,
but I still can't believe it.

1924
01:13:59,334 --> 01:14:01,637
How did they make all these in 15 minutes?

1925
01:14:01,703 --> 01:14:03,038
I still can't believe it.

1926
01:14:03,105 --> 01:14:05,707
What did you think about this round?

1927
01:14:05,774 --> 01:14:07,409
These dishes…

1928
01:14:07,476 --> 01:14:10,012
look completely different from mine.

1929
01:14:10,078 --> 01:14:11,346
How so?

1930
01:14:12,448 --> 01:14:14,483
SPOT THE DIFFERENCE

1931
01:14:14,550 --> 01:14:17,085
They make me want to take pictures.

1932
01:14:17,152 --> 01:14:18,520
Did you not take pictures earlier?

1933
01:14:18,587 --> 01:14:20,289
I forgot…

1934
01:14:21,356 --> 01:14:22,658
Should I make it again?

1935
01:14:23,225 --> 01:14:24,293
Yes…

1936
01:14:24,359 --> 01:14:28,530
I've worked with Hyun-suk
since our first episode,

1937
01:14:28,597 --> 01:14:30,999
and I've never heard him say
something like this.

1938
01:14:31,066 --> 01:14:33,235
"Why didn't you come
for the five-minute check?"

1939
01:14:33,302 --> 01:14:35,504
-Really?
-He didn't notice.

1940
01:14:35,571 --> 01:14:36,905
I didn't know.

1941
01:14:37,806 --> 01:14:39,308
Did we not do the five-minute check today?

1942
01:14:39,374 --> 01:14:41,677
-You don't remember anything?
-I don't.

1943
01:14:41,743 --> 01:14:43,245
-Did we?
-We did.

1944
01:14:44,146 --> 01:14:46,782
That means he was completely focused.

1945
01:14:46,849 --> 01:14:48,884
-He was.
-He didn't even notice it.

1946
01:14:48,951 --> 01:14:50,619
He's now on another level.

1947
01:14:51,253 --> 01:14:52,888
Chef Hyun-suk finished cooking first.

1948
01:14:52,955 --> 01:14:54,223
Legendary Choi's.

1949
01:14:54,289 --> 01:14:56,658
FIVE-RINGS PASTA AND RAVIOLI
DUNKED IN TRUFFLE CREAM

1950
01:14:57,259 --> 01:14:59,862
AND SWEET TIRAMISU AS DESSERT

1951
01:15:00,229 --> 01:15:03,966
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S LEGENDARY CHOI'S

1952
01:15:04,600 --> 01:15:06,368
She waited ten years for this.

1953
01:15:06,935 --> 01:15:08,604
It's such a shame to eat this.

1954
01:15:09,404 --> 01:15:11,273
IT'S A SHAME,
BUT SHE QUICKLY TAKES A SPOONFUL

1955
01:15:11,340 --> 01:15:13,175
The one she brought from Italy.

1956
01:15:13,242 --> 01:15:14,610
RIGHT INTO HER MOUTH!

1957
01:15:14,676 --> 01:15:15,677
The five-rings pasta.

1958
01:15:16,912 --> 01:15:18,013
Immediately.

1959
01:15:18,080 --> 01:15:20,916
-That pasta was on the news.
-It was!

1960
01:15:20,983 --> 01:15:24,720
They only made 2,026 boxes
of that five-rings pasta.

1961
01:15:24,786 --> 01:15:26,955
I really love truffles,

1962
01:15:27,022 --> 01:15:29,491
and I love how it has a strong smell.

1963
01:15:29,625 --> 01:15:31,293
IT LOOKS GOOD

1964
01:15:31,360 --> 01:15:35,397
How did he make ravioli in 15 minutes?

1965
01:15:35,464 --> 01:15:36,865
-He makes it happen.
-Yes.

1966
01:15:36,932 --> 01:15:38,400
-That's Hyun-suk.
-Right.

1967
01:15:38,467 --> 01:15:40,969
How did you win seven medals?

1968
01:15:41,036 --> 01:15:42,638
-Right?
-Yes.

1969
01:15:44,506 --> 01:15:46,174
NODDING

1970
01:15:46,241 --> 01:15:48,043
This is really good. I mean it.

1971
01:15:48,110 --> 01:15:51,313
-The ravioli?
-I can't believe he made it in 15 minutes.

1972
01:15:51,547 --> 01:15:52,548
NERVOUS, AT EASE

1973
01:15:52,614 --> 01:15:55,017
-It's really good.
-I see.

1974
01:15:55,083 --> 01:15:56,218
How well is it cooked?

1975
01:15:56,285 --> 01:15:57,553
Perfectly.

1976
01:15:57,619 --> 01:15:58,954
Is it made with beef?

1977
01:15:59,021 --> 01:16:02,324
Yes, I used beef, onion, arugula,

1978
01:16:02,391 --> 01:16:04,393
<i>and cream cheese to make the filling.</i>

1979
01:16:04,459 --> 01:16:06,562
What's the texture like?

1980
01:16:06,628 --> 01:16:09,364
The texture and the seasoning are perfect.

1981
01:16:09,431 --> 01:16:12,501
It's not something I can judge.
It's that good.

1982
01:16:12,568 --> 01:16:13,669
I'm in shock.

1983
01:16:13,735 --> 01:16:15,170
It's literally perfect.

1984
01:16:15,904 --> 01:16:17,806
That's Hyun-suk for you.

1985
01:16:17,873 --> 01:16:19,107
-Next, the tiramisu.
-You can use this.

1986
01:16:19,174 --> 01:16:20,175
Thank you.

1987
01:16:20,242 --> 01:16:22,144
Scoop it all the way down.

1988
01:16:22,210 --> 01:16:23,946
-Scoop it.
-With the bread.

1989
01:16:24,012 --> 01:16:27,049
-She didn't have many ingredients.
-She didn't.

1990
01:16:27,115 --> 01:16:28,750
-The tiramisu.
-Will it taste like it?

1991
01:16:30,419 --> 01:16:31,987
It must be good.

1992
01:16:32,487 --> 01:16:33,589
Does it taste like it?

1993
01:16:33,655 --> 01:16:35,724
Totally. It's just tiramisu.

1994
01:16:35,791 --> 01:16:37,926
-It's just tiramisu?
-Yes, it's just tiramisu.

1995
01:16:37,993 --> 01:16:39,995
How did he do this in time?

1996
01:16:40,062 --> 01:16:43,198
<i>He had to try so hard</i>
<i>to make that white cream.</i>

1997
01:16:43,265 --> 01:16:44,800
It was…

1998
01:16:44,866 --> 01:16:48,370
It was worth a decade of wait.

1999
01:16:48,437 --> 01:16:49,871
It's that good.

2000
01:16:50,172 --> 01:16:51,707
INDEED, THE BOSS OF CHEF & MY FRIDGE

2001
01:16:51,773 --> 01:16:53,408
Yes, that's Hyun-suk.

2002
01:16:53,475 --> 01:16:56,011
He waited 55 years for this.

2003
01:16:56,078 --> 01:16:57,946
I've watched him since the early days,

2004
01:16:58,013 --> 01:17:00,582
so his dish tastes even better.

2005
01:17:00,649 --> 01:17:02,784
I can't believe he did this in 15 minutes.

2006
01:17:02,851 --> 01:17:04,086
I'm so moved.

2007
01:17:04,152 --> 01:17:09,191
This was definitely worth
getting seven medals for.

2008
01:17:09,257 --> 01:17:12,260
-Really? I'm glad.
-Yes, it's that good.

2009
01:17:12,327 --> 01:17:14,196
-That's Hyun-suk.
-It's so good.

2010
01:17:14,262 --> 01:17:16,832
Chef Jong-won made three different dishes.

2011
01:17:18,400 --> 01:17:19,901
<i>Beef carpaccio,</i>

2012
01:17:20,836 --> 01:17:23,138
<i>minestrone with five-rings pasta,</i>

2013
01:17:24,172 --> 01:17:26,141
<i>and baked Milan.</i>

2014
01:17:27,743 --> 01:17:31,880
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S WHAT DID MIN-JEONG SAY
AFTER WINNING 7 MEDAL-RINGUES?

2015
01:17:31,947 --> 01:17:33,181
How should she begin?

2016
01:17:33,248 --> 01:17:35,517
-The carpaccio first.
-The carpaccio first.

2017
01:17:35,584 --> 01:17:38,687
-It's a rose.
-He made a rose.

2018
01:17:38,754 --> 01:17:42,491
I like carpaccio, but I've never had it
in the shape of a rose.

2019
01:17:42,557 --> 01:17:43,959
So romantic.

2020
01:17:44,026 --> 01:17:46,261
Why did you turn it into a rose?

2021
01:17:46,328 --> 01:17:48,363
I would've made her
a whole bouquet, if I could.

2022
01:17:49,798 --> 01:17:51,500
HIS SMOOTH WORDS WORK WONDERS

2023
01:17:51,566 --> 01:17:54,236
-He's melting her with his words.
-He is.

2024
01:17:54,302 --> 01:17:55,837
-Such sweet talk.
-Not bad.

2025
01:17:55,904 --> 01:17:59,041
-He's gotten so smooth over the year.
-He's all warmed up now.

2026
01:17:59,107 --> 01:18:00,375
How's the carpaccio?

2027
01:18:00,876 --> 01:18:02,878
It's delicious. I love truffles,

2028
01:18:02,944 --> 01:18:05,514
<i>and that must be why he sprinkled</i>
<i>lots of truffle oil.</i>

2029
01:18:05,580 --> 01:18:08,016
Also, this napa cabbage

2030
01:18:08,083 --> 01:18:09,418
makes this even more perfect.

2031
01:18:09,484 --> 01:18:10,919
Is the beef tough at all?

2032
01:18:10,986 --> 01:18:14,389
-Not at all. It melts in my mouth.
-It melts?

2033
01:18:14,456 --> 01:18:16,825
<i>Also, he made it into a flower</i>
<i>despite the lack of time.</i>

2034
01:18:16,892 --> 01:18:18,427
<i>It's like a work of art.</i>

2035
01:18:18,493 --> 01:18:20,862
-He has that sensibility.
-He does.

2036
01:18:20,929 --> 01:18:22,431
-Yes.
-It's so good.

2037
01:18:22,497 --> 01:18:25,600
-What's next?
-Minestrone.

2038
01:18:25,667 --> 01:18:27,569
-Minestrone, veggie soup.
-With five-rings pasta.

2039
01:18:27,636 --> 01:18:29,471
Minestrone with five-rings pasta.

2040
01:18:30,005 --> 01:18:31,139
Italian vegetable soup.

2041
01:18:33,675 --> 01:18:35,944
Are these tomatoes and…

2042
01:18:36,011 --> 01:18:37,212
What's in here?

2043
01:18:37,279 --> 01:18:39,347
-<i>You had Ragú…</i>
-<i>Ragú.</i>

2044
01:18:39,414 --> 01:18:41,383
-<i>…so I threw that in with some veggies.</i>
-<i>She had Ragú?</i>

2045
01:18:41,450 --> 01:18:44,186
And I used canned ham
to quickly extract a stock.

2046
01:18:44,252 --> 01:18:46,221
-I see.
-To add flavor.

2047
01:18:46,288 --> 01:18:47,589
I see. Stock from canned ham?

2048
01:18:47,656 --> 01:18:50,292
It's made with ham
like pancetta, originally.

2049
01:18:50,358 --> 01:18:52,027
-He ground it.
-It has a deep flavor,

2050
01:18:52,094 --> 01:18:54,329
-and it's shockingly delicious.
-To use as broth.

2051
01:18:54,396 --> 01:18:56,098
-The broth.
-He used it as stock.

2052
01:18:56,164 --> 01:18:57,799
Lastly…

2053
01:18:57,866 --> 01:18:59,401
-The dessert.
-The dessert.

2054
01:18:59,468 --> 01:19:02,237
-One second.
-There's one addition for baked Alaska.

2055
01:19:02,304 --> 01:19:05,574
-It needs alcohol on top.
-Over the top?

2056
01:19:05,640 --> 01:19:08,510
-Is that a thing?
-It's called baked Alaska

2057
01:19:08,577 --> 01:19:10,645
-because the place is cold.
-It is.

2058
01:19:11,213 --> 01:19:12,948
-You're adding alcohol?
-Warm.

2059
01:19:13,014 --> 01:19:15,417
-You're serving warm alcohol?
-He's going to set it on fire.

2060
01:19:15,484 --> 01:19:17,119
He'll set it on fire?

2061
01:19:17,185 --> 01:19:19,054
THE FIRE BURNS BRIGHTLY
JUST LIKE A TORCH

2062
01:19:19,121 --> 01:19:20,522
It's on fire.

2063
01:19:20,589 --> 01:19:21,890
LOOKING FORWARD TO IT

2064
01:19:22,090 --> 01:19:23,291
ABLAZE

2065
01:19:23,358 --> 01:19:25,861
Now, Baked Alaska.

2066
01:19:25,927 --> 01:19:27,362
CARRYING IT AS PRECIOUSLY AS A TORCH

2067
01:19:27,429 --> 01:19:29,464
-So this is how it's served.
-Stay still, please.

2068
01:19:31,967 --> 01:19:33,435
This is how it's served?

2069
01:19:33,502 --> 01:19:35,237
FIERY ALCOHOL OVER THE MERINGUE

2070
01:19:35,303 --> 01:19:37,339
The hot alcohol cooks the meringue.

2071
01:19:37,839 --> 01:19:40,442
-Like that?
-That cooks the meringue?

2072
01:19:42,277 --> 01:19:44,246
-I've never seen anything like this.
-She's never seen it.

2073
01:19:44,312 --> 01:19:47,382
He carried it like a torch.

2074
01:19:47,449 --> 01:19:50,485
-It's giving off sporty vibes.
-It really does.

2075
01:19:50,552 --> 01:19:52,287
The contrast of hot and cold.

2076
01:19:52,354 --> 01:19:55,957
You'll find ice cream and strawberry
down the middle.

2077
01:19:56,258 --> 01:19:58,360
IT LOOKS SO GOOD

2078
01:19:58,426 --> 01:20:00,262
He said this was cold inside…

2079
01:20:00,328 --> 01:20:02,664
-And hot outside.
-…and hot outside.

2080
01:20:02,731 --> 01:20:03,765
YUM

2081
01:20:03,832 --> 01:20:05,033
Hot outside, cold inside.

2082
01:20:05,100 --> 01:20:06,501
WIDE-EYED

2083
01:20:07,636 --> 01:20:09,905
This can't be bad. It's amazing.

2084
01:20:09,971 --> 01:20:11,873
-It can't be bad.
-It can't be bad.

2085
01:20:11,940 --> 01:20:12,941
What's it like?

2086
01:20:13,008 --> 01:20:17,612
He mixed two of my favorites,
strawberries and vanilla ice cream.

2087
01:20:17,679 --> 01:20:20,749
I like to eat things that have
many flavors in one bite,

2088
01:20:20,816 --> 01:20:22,984
and this felt hot, cold,

2089
01:20:23,051 --> 01:20:25,754
sweet, and sour at the same time.

2090
01:20:25,821 --> 01:20:27,722
It's really good.

2091
01:20:27,789 --> 01:20:30,258
She's in trouble. Everything is good.

2092
01:20:30,325 --> 01:20:32,494
-Yes, what am I going to do?
-What now?

2093
01:20:32,561 --> 01:20:33,995
-That looks good.
-That looks good.

2094
01:20:34,062 --> 01:20:35,797
-That looks good.
-That looks good.

2095
01:20:36,798 --> 01:20:38,633
They're all drooling.

2096
01:20:38,700 --> 01:20:42,504
She's going back and forth
between five different dishes.

2097
01:20:42,571 --> 01:20:43,905
I'm jealous.

2098
01:20:43,972 --> 01:20:45,540
You waited ten years for these.

2099
01:20:45,607 --> 01:20:48,777
-Take your time.
-Take your time and decide at ease.

2100
01:20:48,844 --> 01:20:51,079
You should try some too, Gil-li.

2101
01:20:51,146 --> 01:20:52,848
That's Chef Hyun-suk's dish.

2102
01:20:52,914 --> 01:20:54,216
It looks good.

2103
01:20:54,282 --> 01:20:56,218
WHAT DOES THE FIVE-RINGS PASTA TASTE LIKE?

2104
01:20:58,553 --> 01:21:00,021
Do you understand what she meant?

2105
01:21:00,088 --> 01:21:01,089
A BITE OF CARPACCIO

2106
01:21:01,156 --> 01:21:03,992
I've had this pasta before,

2107
01:21:04,059 --> 01:21:07,729
but it was awful back in the cafeteria.

2108
01:21:07,796 --> 01:21:09,631
So I didn't get my hopes up.

2109
01:21:10,866 --> 01:21:14,803
This was how they were
supposed to cook pasta.

2110
01:21:14,870 --> 01:21:16,071
They didn't do it right.

2111
01:21:16,137 --> 01:21:18,974
I must've eaten something
that wasn't cooked well.

2112
01:21:19,040 --> 01:21:21,943
-Of course.
-Our chefs do things proper.

2113
01:21:22,444 --> 01:21:23,712
Next, tiramisu.

2114
01:21:23,778 --> 01:21:25,480
He created it from nothing.

2115
01:21:27,249 --> 01:21:28,416
Does it taste like tiramisu?

2116
01:21:28,984 --> 01:21:30,285
Gosh, no way.

2117
01:21:30,352 --> 01:21:32,587
-"Gosh, no way."
-"Gosh, no way."

2118
01:21:32,654 --> 01:21:35,156
This cream is so delicious.

2119
01:21:35,223 --> 01:21:37,726
-It's so good.
-He didn't even know I was up there.

2120
01:21:37,792 --> 01:21:39,027
-Is it that good?
-Yes.

2121
01:21:39,094 --> 01:21:41,329
Next, Chef Jong-won's dishes.

2122
01:21:41,830 --> 01:21:45,433
She must've had lots of different foods
while traveling abroad to compete.

2123
01:21:45,934 --> 01:21:49,371
The balance between the beef
and cabbage is very good.

2124
01:21:49,437 --> 01:21:51,539
And the dash of truffle

2125
01:21:52,407 --> 01:21:53,842
is awesome.

2126
01:21:54,042 --> 01:21:55,043
HOW CUTE

2127
01:21:55,110 --> 01:21:56,578
Is it awesome?

2128
01:21:56,645 --> 01:21:57,746
AWESOME

2129
01:21:57,812 --> 01:22:00,615
-It's really good. Yes.
-Is it that good?

2130
01:22:01,449 --> 01:22:04,019
-Baked Milan.
-It looks good.

2131
01:22:04,586 --> 01:22:05,754
Gosh, no way.

2132
01:22:05,820 --> 01:22:07,022
-"Gosh, no way."
-"Gosh, no way."

2133
01:22:07,088 --> 01:22:08,490
-"Gosh, no way."
-"Gosh, no way."

2134
01:22:09,057 --> 01:22:10,892
He used a meringue machine.

2135
01:22:10,959 --> 01:22:13,261
Yes, and he used alcohol too.

2136
01:22:13,328 --> 01:22:14,562
What's it like?

2137
01:22:14,629 --> 01:22:16,798
Is it because I like cream?

2138
01:22:16,865 --> 01:22:19,000
I love the mix of the cream
and the ice cream,

2139
01:22:19,067 --> 01:22:20,635
and I also like strawberries, so…

2140
01:22:22,003 --> 01:22:25,006
-It's awesome.
-It's awesome.

2141
01:22:25,073 --> 01:22:28,944
And now, you must make the choice
you waited a decade to make.

2142
01:22:29,010 --> 01:22:31,579
It's much harder to choose
because I watched them

2143
01:22:31,646 --> 01:22:34,683
-throughout the cooking process.
-Right?

2144
01:22:34,749 --> 01:22:37,118
-They did their best.
-But you must still choose.

2145
01:22:37,185 --> 01:22:38,553
You cannot avoid this.

2146
01:22:38,620 --> 01:22:41,957
<i>Press one to choose Jong-won,</i>

2147
01:22:42,023 --> 01:22:44,960
<i>and two to choose Hyun-suk.</i>

2148
01:22:45,026 --> 01:22:47,495
Please make your choice
and press the button!

2149
01:22:48,863 --> 01:22:49,864
What do I do?

2150
01:22:51,800 --> 01:22:54,302
-You had fun until now, didn't you?
-Wait.

2151
01:22:54,369 --> 01:22:57,339
-I did press a button.
-You did?

2152
01:22:57,405 --> 01:22:59,341
I hope you won't take this the wrong way.

2153
01:22:59,407 --> 01:23:02,210
I couldn't dare to judge
on how these tasted.

2154
01:23:02,277 --> 01:23:04,879
-Everyone says that.
-I just…

2155
01:23:04,946 --> 01:23:07,048
-They all say that.
-Everyone says that.

2156
01:23:07,115 --> 01:23:08,783
Before we check the result,

2157
01:23:08,850 --> 01:23:12,487
Min-jeong, who waited
ten years to appear on the show,

2158
01:23:12,554 --> 01:23:14,122
wants to give

2159
01:23:14,189 --> 01:23:15,590
the chefs and the production crew

2160
01:23:15,657 --> 01:23:16,658
a present.

2161
01:23:16,725 --> 01:23:18,226
-What?
-What is it?

2162
01:23:18,293 --> 01:23:20,862
I was so grateful and moved

2163
01:23:20,929 --> 01:23:23,598
to see the chefs cook
in such a short time,

2164
01:23:23,665 --> 01:23:26,368
so I'll make use
of my fried chicken pension

2165
01:23:26,434 --> 01:23:30,405
and treat you to some fried chicken
during your next shoot.

2166
01:23:30,472 --> 01:23:31,473
YESSS!

2167
01:23:33,108 --> 01:23:35,410
-We get free chicken!
-Fried chicken!

2168
01:23:35,477 --> 01:23:37,412
THANK YOU

2169
01:23:37,479 --> 01:23:39,347
How many chickens will you eat, Nam-no?

2170
01:23:39,414 --> 01:23:41,216
-Me? Two or three.
-Two or three?

2171
01:23:41,282 --> 01:23:42,283
Are you on a diet?

2172
01:23:42,350 --> 01:23:43,952
A chicken diet.

2173
01:23:44,019 --> 01:23:46,454
Let's find out the result. Show us!

2174
01:23:46,521 --> 01:23:48,556
The winner of this round

2175
01:23:48,623 --> 01:23:50,725
might as well be the one
who gets Min-jeong's medal.

2176
01:23:50,792 --> 01:23:52,293
-You're right.
-Yes.

2177
01:23:52,360 --> 01:23:55,964
-Hyun-suk waited 55 years for Min-jeong.
-Yes, Choi Hyun-suk!

2178
01:23:56,031 --> 01:23:57,032
Fifty-five years.

2179
01:23:57,098 --> 01:24:00,869
Or will it be Jong-won,
who prepared a flower for her?

2180
01:24:00,935 --> 01:24:02,337
Who did Min-jeong choose?

2181
01:24:02,904 --> 01:24:04,472
Which one will it be?

2182
01:24:04,539 --> 01:24:08,743
Which chef will receive her star?

2183
01:24:08,810 --> 01:24:10,078
Who's the winner?

2184
01:24:10,145 --> 01:24:11,880
SON JONG-WON WINS

2185
01:24:11,946 --> 01:24:14,215
WHAT DID MIN-JEONG SAY
AFTER WINNING 7 MEDAL-RINGUES? WINS

2186
01:24:14,282 --> 01:24:15,383
Son Jong-won wins!

2187
01:24:15,450 --> 01:24:17,252
-Great round.
-It's Jong-won.

2188
01:24:18,820 --> 01:24:21,623
She chose Jong-won.

2189
01:24:21,689 --> 01:24:24,125
Chef Hyun-suk's dish

2190
01:24:24,192 --> 01:24:28,129
was so delicious that
it was worth waiting for a decade.

2191
01:24:28,196 --> 01:24:30,098
But Chef Jong-won's dish

2192
01:24:30,165 --> 01:24:31,499
was so good

2193
01:24:31,566 --> 01:24:35,336
that I was almost tempted
to take back my last dance

2194
01:24:35,403 --> 01:24:38,940
and participate in the games again
in four years just to eat this.

2195
01:24:39,007 --> 01:24:40,742
Also, it was the dessert.

2196
01:24:40,809 --> 01:24:43,011
It was quite mind-blowing.

2197
01:24:43,078 --> 01:24:47,115
It was a kind of dessert
I have never had in my life.

2198
01:24:47,682 --> 01:24:50,018
And now, Min-jeong the legendary skater,

2199
01:24:50,085 --> 01:24:53,021
please put a star on Chef Son Jong-won!

2200
01:24:54,489 --> 01:24:56,458
-Thank you.
-Great work.

2201
01:24:56,524 --> 01:24:57,859
-Thank you.
-It was delicious.

2202
01:24:57,926 --> 01:25:00,562
And this. The kit.

2203
01:25:00,628 --> 01:25:04,099
-Thank you.
-Pose for a picture.

2204
01:25:04,165 --> 01:25:05,900
Congratulations!

2205
01:25:05,967 --> 01:25:07,969
-Where do I look?
-No idea. Over there.

2206
01:25:09,037 --> 01:25:10,805
-He's back.
-He's here!

2207
01:25:10,872 --> 01:25:13,842
He returns in glory
after winning the competition!

2208
01:25:13,908 --> 01:25:16,010
"Just bring the doll home."

2209
01:25:16,077 --> 01:25:17,779
-We'll give it when he wins.
-Great idea.

2210
01:25:17,846 --> 01:25:19,981
Eek. I didn't expect that move.

2211
01:25:20,281 --> 01:25:21,316
WE GOT YOU

2212
01:25:21,382 --> 01:25:22,917
Please welcome today's fridge owners,

2213
01:25:22,984 --> 01:25:25,553
Nana and Kyuhyun! Come on out!

2214
01:25:25,620 --> 01:25:27,288
She changes when she dances.

2215
01:25:27,355 --> 01:25:29,190
Do you have any secrets to your diet?

2216
01:25:29,257 --> 01:25:30,992
I eat butter on an empty stomach.

2217
01:25:31,059 --> 01:25:32,060
Doesn't it feel greasy?

2218
01:25:32,127 --> 01:25:33,962
It's actually better than you think.

2219
01:25:34,028 --> 01:25:35,463
She eats this on an empty stomach.

2220
01:25:35,530 --> 01:25:37,065
It tastes like a candle.

2221
01:25:37,132 --> 01:25:38,166
COUGH

2222
01:25:38,233 --> 01:25:39,534
THE TOUGHEST DIET EVER

2223
01:25:39,601 --> 01:25:40,835
A dish just for Nana.

2224
01:25:41,136 --> 01:25:42,337
MAGICAL CHEFS ARE HERE

2225
01:25:42,504 --> 01:25:43,905
PLAYING HIS HIDDEN MOVE

2226
01:25:44,139 --> 01:25:45,173
FAINTING

2227
01:25:45,406 --> 01:25:47,142
A BIG MAKEOVER FOR HER INGREDIENTS

2228
01:25:47,208 --> 01:25:48,343
MMM

2229
01:25:48,409 --> 01:25:49,677
A MAGICAL DISH

2230
01:25:49,744 --> 01:25:51,179
A HEALTHY DISH COOK-OFF

2231
01:25:51,246 --> 01:25:52,714
He's using that much butter?

2232
01:25:52,780 --> 01:25:54,015
It's for Nana's health.

2233
01:25:54,215 --> 01:25:55,283
LOVES IT

2234
01:25:55,350 --> 01:25:56,651
<i>I've returned as Amy Park.</i>

2235
01:25:56,885 --> 01:25:57,886
BURNING

2236
01:25:57,952 --> 01:25:59,254
Do Western dishes need smoky flavors?

2237
01:25:59,320 --> 01:26:00,355
DOESN'T CARE, OYSTER SAUCE

2238
01:26:00,421 --> 01:26:01,523
MAKING OTHER CHEFS SHUDDER

2239
01:26:02,056 --> 01:26:03,458
HOW WILL THIS UNPREDICTABLE ROUND GO?

2240
01:26:06,728 --> 01:26:07,729
What is that?

2241
01:26:09,697 --> 01:26:11,533
WHAT HAS HAPPENED IN THE LAST YEAR?

2242
01:26:21,209 --> 01:26:26,214
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
